\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 24950000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 24950000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-cuAaDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 24.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 24.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/cuAaDgAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Exceptional_America-sample-pdf.acsm?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Exceptional_America-sample-epub.acsm?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In this provocative book, Mugambi Jouet describes why Americans are far more divided than other Westerners over basic issues, including wealth inequality, health care, climate change, evolution, gender roles, abortion, gay rights, sex, gun ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Exceptional America\", \"authors\": [\"Mugambi Jouet\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"What Divides Americans from the World and from Each Other\", \"pageCount\": 358, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Univ of California Press\", \"categories\": [\"Social Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Why did Donald Trump follow Barack Obama into the White House? Why is America so polarized? And how does American exceptionalism explain these social changes? In this provocative book, Mugambi Jouet describes why Americans are far more divided than other Westerners over basic issues, including wealth inequality, health care, climate change, evolution, gender roles, abortion, gay rights, sex, gun control, mass incarceration, the death penalty, torture, human rights, and war. Raised in Paris by a French mother and Kenyan father, Jouet then lived in the Bible Belt, Manhattan, and beyond. Drawing inspiration from Alexis de Tocqueville, he wields his multicultural sensibility to parse how the intense polarization of U.S. conservatives and liberals has become a key dimension of American exceptionalism—an idea widely misunderstood as American superiority. While exceptionalism once was a source of strength, it may now spell decline, as unique features of U.S. history, politics, law, culture, religion, and race relations foster grave conflicts. They also shed light on the intriguing ideological evolution of American conservatism, which long predated Trumpism. Anti-intellectualism, conspiracy-mongering, a visceral suspicion of government, and Christian fundamentalism are far more common in America than the rest of the Western world—Europe, Canada, Australia, and New Zealand. Exceptional America dissects the American soul, in all of its peculiar, clashing, and striking manifestations.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=america&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2017-04-03\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.2.2.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=cuAaDgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780520966468\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0520966465\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"unKNDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"2yg7LZDh2Ck\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-unKNDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/unKNDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Songs_of_America-sample-epub.acsm?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Meacham chronicles our history, exploring the stories behind the songs, and Tim McGraw reflects on them as an artist and performer.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Songs of America\", \"authors\": [\"Jon Meacham\", \"Tim McGraw\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Patriotism, Protest, and the Music That Made a Nation\", \"pageCount\": 320, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Random House\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"NEW YORK TIMES BESTSELLER • A celebration of American history through the music that helped to shape a nation, by Pulitzer Prize winner Jon Meacham and music superstar Tim McGraw “Jon Meacham and Tim McGraw form an irresistible duo—connecting us to music as an unsung force in our nation\'s history.”—Doris Kearns Goodwin Through all the years of strife and triumph, America has been shaped not just by our elected leaders and our formal politics but also by our music—by the lyrics, performers, and instrumentals that have helped to carry us through the dark days and to celebrate the bright ones. From “The Star-Spangled Banner” to “Born in the U.S.A.,” Jon Meacham and Tim McGraw take readers on a moving and insightful journey through eras in American history and the songs and performers that inspired us. Meacham chronicles our history, exploring the stories behind the songs, and Tim McGraw reflects on them as an artist and performer. Their perspectives combine to create a unique view of the role music has played in uniting and shaping a nation. Beginning with the battle hymns of the revolution, and taking us through songs from the defining events of the Civil War, the fight for women’s suffrage, the two world wars, the Great Depression, the civil rights movement, the Vietnam War, and into the twenty-first century, Meacham and McGraw explore the songs that defined generations, and the cultural and political climates that produced them. Readers will discover the power of music in the lives of figures such as Harriet Tubman, Franklin Roosevelt, Eleanor Roosevelt, and Martin Luther King, Jr., and will learn more about some of our most beloved musicians and performers, including Marian Anderson, Elvis Presley, Sam Cooke, Aretha Franklin, Bob Dylan, Duke Ellington, Carole King, Bruce Springsteen, and more. Songs of America explores both famous songs and lesser-known ones, expanding our understanding of the scope of American music and lending deeper meaning to the historical context of such songs as “My Country, ’Tis of Thee,” “God Bless America,” “Over There,” “We Shall Overcome,” and “Blowin’ in the Wind.” As Quincy Jones says, Meacham and McGraw have “convened a concert in Songs of America,” one that reminds us of who we are, where we’ve been, and what we, at our best, can be.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=america&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 7, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2019-06-11\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.3.2.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=unKNDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780593132968\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0593132963\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 3474}'),('angels','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"sDUbiV92-mIC\", \"etag\": \"Nv07nUAsmZ4\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \