t?id=E8hPAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E8hPAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"In Buildings of Iowa, David Gebhard and Gerald Mansheim trace Iowa\'s architectural history from the earliest Native American influences to the present. Divided into five regional areas--Mississippi River East, Mississippi River West, and the Central, South, and North regions--the book\'s entries within each area are presented on a town-by-town basis to include the full array of Iowa\'s architectural offerings in various styles. Whether discussing farm houses, barns, and silos or churches, schools, courthouses, and libraries, the volume shows how a unity of rural and urban is effectively mirrored in Iowa\'s buildings.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=E8hPAAAAMAAJ&q=buildings&dq=buildings&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"1993\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.2.1.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Buildings_of_Iowa.html?hl=&id=E8hPAAAAMAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"OTHER\", \"identifier\": \"UOM:39015020881333\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"z4JQAAAAMAAJ\", \"etag\": \"YWN1UiVBRc4\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/z4JQAAAAMAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=z4JQAAAAMAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"An &quot;anatomical&quot; study of building systems integration with guidelines for practical applications Through a systems approach to buildings, Integrated Buildings: The Systems Basis of Architecture details the practice of integration to bridge ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Integrated Buildings\", \"authors\": [\"Leonard R. Bachman\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=z4JQAAAAMAAJ&dq=buildings&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Systems Basis of Architecture\", \"pageCount\": 480, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"John Wiley & Sons\", \"categories\": [\"Architecture\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=z4JQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=z4JQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"An \\\"anatomical\\\" study of building systems integration with guidelines for practical applications Through a systems approach to buildings, Integrated Buildings: The Systems Basis of Architecture details the practice of integration to bridge the gap between the design intentions and technical demands of building projects. Analytic methods are introduced that illustrate the value, benefit, and application of systems integration, as well as guidelines for selecting technical systems in the conceptual, schematic, and design development stages of projects. Landmark structures such as Eero Saarinen\'s John Deere Headquarters, Renzo Piano\'s Kansai International Airport, Glenn Murcutt\'s Magney House, and Richard Rogers\'s Lloyd\'s of London headquarters are presented as part of an extensive collection of case studies organized into seven categories: Laboratories Offices Pavilions Green Architecture High Tech Architecture Airport Terminals Residential Architecture Advanced material is provided on methods of integration, including an overview of integration topics, the systems basis of architecture, and the integration potential of various building systems. An expanded case study of Ibsen Nelsen\'s design for the Pacific Museum of Flight is used to demonstrate case study methods for tracing integration through any work of architecture. Visually enhanced with more than 300 illustrations, diagrams, and photographs, Integrated Buildings: The Systems Basis of Architecture is a valuable reference guide for architecture and civil engineering students, as well as architects, engineers, and other professionals in the construction industry.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=z4JQAAAAMAAJ&q=buildings&dq=buildings&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2003\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.6.2.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Integrated_Buildings.html?hl=&id=z4JQAAAAMAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"OTHER\", \"identifier\": \"UOM:39015056243887\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"7-Cj7c_Nv08C\", \"etag\": \"jI6OIZmy7tI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 150000000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 120000000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}, {\"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 75000000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 66000000}, \"rentalDuration\": {\"unit\": \"DAY\", \"count\": 180}, \"finskyOfferType\": 3}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=7-Cj7c_Nv08C&rdid=book-7-Cj7c_Nv08C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\"