ging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Chinese_National_Cinema.html?hl=&id=70wmf8_nYTcC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"041517290X\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780415172905\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"gQF8kvWmFJkC\", \"etag\": \"6l9gDx1JqyE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/gQF8kvWmFJkC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Chinese_Language-sample-pdf.acsm?id=gQF8kvWmFJkC&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=gQF8kvWmFJkC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This is a book for everyone.&quot; --Joshua A. Fishman, research professor of social sciences, Yeshiva University, New York &quot;Professor De Francis has produced a work of great effectiveness that should appeal to a wide-ranging audience.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Chinese Language\", \"authors\": [\"John DeFrancis\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=gQF8kvWmFJkC&dq=chinese&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Fact and Fantasy\", \"pageCount\": 342, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Hawaii Press\", \"categories\": [\"Foreign Language Study\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gQF8kvWmFJkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gQF8kvWmFJkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"\\\"DeFrancis\'s book is first rate. It entertains. It teaches. It demystifies. It counteracts popular ignorance as well as sophisticated (cocktail party) ignorance. Who could ask for anything more? There is no other book like it. ... It is one of a kind, a first, and I would not only buy it but I would recommend it to friends and colleagues, many of whom are visiting China now and are adding \'two-week-expert\' ignorance to the two kinds that existed before. This is a book for everyone.\\\" --Joshua A. Fishman, research professor of social sciences, Yeshiva University, New York \\\"Professor De Francis has produced a work of great effectiveness that should appeal to a wide-ranging audience. It is at once instructive and entertaining. While being delighted by the flair of his novel approach, the reader will also be led to ponder on some of the most fundamental problems concerning the relations between written languages and spoken languages. Specifically, he will be served a variety of information on the languages of East Asia, not as dry pedantic facts, but as appealing tidbits that whet the intellectual appetite. The expert will find much to reflect on in this book, for Professor DeFrancis takes nothing for granted.\\\" --William S.Y. Wang, professor of linguistics, University of California at Berkeley\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=gQF8kvWmFJkC&printsec=frontcover&dq=chinese&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 2, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"1986-03-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.3.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Chinese_Language.html?hl=&id=gQF8kvWmFJkC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0824810686\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780824810689\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"r7USEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"bGsARFx6c/0\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 17990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 17990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-r7USEAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 17.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 17.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/r7USEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Legendary_Chinese_Festivals-sample-pdf.acsm?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Legendary_Chinese_Festivals-sample-epub.acsm?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This is especially true of Chinese communities outside their homeland.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Legendary Chinese Festivals\", \"authors\": [\"Joey Yap\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 376, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Joey Yap Research Group \", \"categories\": [\"Philosophy\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Chinese culture and heritage is rich and runs across a time frame of five thousand years. It was during this time that a variety of unique and varied celebrations began to grow roots. Despite China’s many changes Chinese festivals are deeply rooted in popular tradition. China amasses a vast area and consists of a number of ethnic groups that all come together as part of a vibrant cultural experience. Some of these festivals have developed into popular celebrations that are not only practiced in China, but also in many Chinese communities throughout the world. Much of the customs and traditions of its people vary by geography and ethnicity yet remain firmly established as part of the country’s vibrant culture. Over the years much of the festivals have evolved with the changes in the development of the Chinese civilization and as a consequence have become an integral part of the Chinese culture. As with time’s progression and the advent of science, technology and rapid globalisation many Chinese are no longer able to tell how their festivals originated which has in turn seen the gradual shedding of ethnic traditions for modern and universal ways. This is especially true of Chinese communities outside their homeland.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=chinese&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-01-08\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=r7USEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9789671739112\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"9671739113\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"NvdAAAAAIAAJ\", \"etag\": \"FSuciaY6sgI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&rdid=book-NvdAAAAAIAAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"saleability\": \"FREE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/NvdAAAAAIAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"downloadLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Chinese_Fairy_Book.pdf?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&hl=&output=pdf&sig=ACfU3U0fv5ARLiMZ-XjNaw8cH2CrsqzlQg&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false, \"downloadLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Chinese_Fairy_Book.epub?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&hl=&output=epub&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"ALL_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": true, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"FULL_PUBLIC_DOMAIN\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The fairy tales and legends of olden China have in common with the &quot;Thousand and One Nights&quot; an oriental glow and glitter of precious stones and gold and multicolored silks, an oriental wealth of fantastic and supernatural action.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Chinese Fairy Book\", \"authors\": [\"Richard Wilhelm\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 329, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Createspace Independent Publishing Platform\", \"categories\": [\"Fairy tales\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The fairy tales and legends of olden China have in common with the \\\"Thousand and One Nights\\\" an oriental glow and glitter of precious stones and gold and multicolored silks, an oriental wealth of fantastic and supernatural action. And yet they strike an exotic note distinct in itself. The seventy-three stories here presented after original sources, embracing \\\"Nursery Fairy Tales,\\\" \\\"Legends of the Gods,\\\" \\\"Tales of Saints and Magicians,\\\" \\\"Nature and Animal Tales,\\\" \\\"Ghost Stories,\\\" \\\"Historic Fairy Tales,\\\" and \\\"Literary Fairy Tales,\\\" probably represent the most comprehensive and varied collection of oriental fairy tales ever made available for American readers. There is no child who will not enjoy their novel color, their fantastic beauty, their infinite variety of subject. Yet, like the \\\"Arabian Nights,\\\" they will amply repay the attention of the older reader as well. Some are exquisitely poetic, such as \\\"The Flower-Elves,\\\" \\\"The Lady of the Moon\\\" or \\\"The Herd Boy and the Weaving Maiden\\\"; others like \\\"How Three Heroes Came By Their Deaths Because Of Two Peaches,\\\" carry us back dramatically and powerfully to the Chinese age of Chivalry. The summits of fantasy are scaled in the quasi-religious dramas of \\\"The Ape Sun Wu Kung\\\" and \\\"Notscha,\\\" or the weird sorceries unfolded in \\\"The Kindly Magician.\\\" Delightful ghost stories, with happy endings, such as \\\"A Night on the Battlefield\\\" and \\\"The Ghost Who Was Foiled,\\\" are paralleled with such idyllic love-tales as that of \\\"Rose of Evening,\\\" or such Lilliputian fancies as \\\"The King of the Ants\\\" and \\\"The Little Hunting Dog.\\\" It is quite safe to say that these Chinese fairy tales will give equal pleasure to the old as well as the young. They have been retold simply, with no changes in style or expression beyond such details of presentation which differences between oriental and occidental viewpoints at times compel. It is the writer\'s hope that others may take as much pleasure in reading them as he did in their translation.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=chinese&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 2, \"publishedDate\": \"1921\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.2.0.full.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NvdAAAAAIAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"OTHER\", \"identifier\": \"UCAL:$B98105\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"K_syEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"SjK3ZF+pBFg\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 32950000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 18120000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-K_syEAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 32.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 18.12, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/K_syEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Chinese_Pleasure_Book-sample-pdf.acsm?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Chinese_Pleasure_Book-sample-epub.acsm?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This book takes up one of the most important themes in Chinese thought: the relation of pleasurable activities to bodily health and to the health of the body politic.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Chinese Pleasure Book\", \"authors\": [\"Michael Nylan\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 472, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Princeton University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Philosophy\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This book takes up one of the most important themes in Chinese thought: the relation of pleasurable activities to bodily health and to the health of the body politic. Unlike Western theories of pleasure, early Chinese writings contrast pleasure not with pain but with insecurity, assuming that it is right and proper to seek and take pleasure, as well as experience short-term delight. Equally important is the belief that certain long-term relational pleasures are more easily sustained, as well as potentially more satisfying and less damaging. The pleasures that become deeper and more ingrained as the person invests time and effort to their cultivation include friendship and music, sharing with others, developing integrity and greater clarity, reading and classical learning, and going home. Each of these activities is explored through the early sources (mainly fourth century BC to the eleventh century AD), with new translations of both well-known and seldom-cited texts.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=chinese&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-09-14\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=K_syEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781942130161\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1942130163\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"n8z_DAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"HRXpXLilYEk\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 4990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 4990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-n8z_DAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 4.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 4.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/n8z_DAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Origins_of_Chinese_Art_Craft-sample-pdf.acsm?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Origins_of_Chinese_Art_Craft-sample-epub.acsm?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Origins of Chinese Art &amp; Craft will give you a quick and easy-to-remember introduction to these works of art with its vivid illustrations and accessible text and cartoons.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Origins of Chinese Art & Craft\", \"authors\": [\"Li Xiaoxiang\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"\", \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Asiapac Books Pte Ltd\", \"categories\": [\"Art\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Find out these interesting details: 1. The Silk Route as well as the Pottery and Porcelain Route of old China. 2. The multitude of Chinese characters and idioms related to jade. 3. The significance of the Qin bronze artefacts unearthed at Lingtong, Shaanxi Province. Origins of Chinese Art & Craft will give you a quick and easy-to-remember introduction to these works of art with its vivid illustrations and accessible text and cartoons.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=chinese&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2013-10-10\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=n8z_DAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9789813170254\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"9813170255\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 3078}'),('college','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"GJvHAgAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"qoHTGtZgoaM\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/GJvHAgAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=GJvHAgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In his foreword to this new edition, John Thelin assesses the impact that Rudolph&#39;s work has had on higher education studies.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The American College and University\", \"authors\": [\"Frederick Rudolph\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=GJvHAgAAQBAJ&dq=college&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A History\", \"pageCount\": 563, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Georgia Press\", \"categories\": [\"Education\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GJvHAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GJvHAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"First published in 1962, Frederick Rudolph\'s groundbreaking study, The American College and University, remains one of the most useful and significant works on the history of higher education in America. Bridging the chasm between educational and social history, this book was one of the first to examine developments in higher education in the context of the social, economic, and political forces that were shaping the nation at large. Surveying higher education from the colonial era through the mid-twentieth century, Rudolph explores a multitude of issues from the financing of institutions and the development of curriculum to the education of women and blacks, the rise of college athletics, and the complexities of student life. In his foreword to this new edition, John Thelin assesses the impact that Rudolph\'s work has had on higher education studies. The new edition also includes a bibliographic essay by Thelin covering significant works in the field that have appeared since the publication of the first edition. At a time when our educational system as a whole is under intense scrutiny, Rudolph\'s seminal work offers an important historical perspective on the development of higher education in the United States.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=GJvHAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"1962\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_American_College_and_University.html?hl=&id=GJvHAgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780820312842\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0820312843\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"hDskDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"sG7SZgVch0M\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/hDskDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=hDskDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"For much of the past century college tuition has risen more rapidly than the inflation rate. Unlike many analyses of higher education, Archibald and Feldman show how broad economic factors have combined to push up cost.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Why Does College Cost So Much?\", \"authors\": [\"Robert B. Archibald\", \"David H. Feldman\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=hDskDwAAQBAJ&dq=college&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 289, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Oxford University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Business & Economics\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hDskDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hDskDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"For much of the past century college tuition has risen more rapidly than the inflation rate. Unlike many analyses of higher education, Archibald and Feldman show how broad economic factors have combined to push up cost. These forces are largely out of the control of colleges and universities.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=hDskDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 2, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"2014-08\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Why_Does_College_Cost_So_Much.html?hl=&id=hDskDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780190214104\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0190214104\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"fUi7DwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"G+BpDs98Ndc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 7990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 7990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-fUi7DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 7.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 7.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/fUi7DwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Come_On_In-sample-epub.acsm?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"WELCOME From some of the most exciting bestselling and up-and-coming YA authors writing today…journey from Ecuador to New York City and Argentina to Utah…from Australia to Harlem and India to New Jersey…from Fiji, America, Mexico and ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Come On In\", \"authors\": [\"Adi Alsaid\", \"Varsha Bajaj\", \"Maria E. Andreu\", \"Sharon Morse\", \"Misa Sugiura\", \"Nafiza Azad\", \"Maurene Goo\", \"Sona Charaipotra\", \"Yamile Saied Méndez\", \"Zoraida Córdova\", \"Alaya Dawn Johnson\", \"Sara Farizan\", \"Isabel Quintero\", \"Justine Larbalestier\", \"Lilliam Rivera\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"15 Stories about Immigration and Finding Home\", \"pageCount\": 304, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Harlequin\", \"categories\": [\"Young Adult Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This exceptional and powerful anthology explores the joys, heartbreaks and triumphs of immigration, with stories by critically acclaimed and bestselling YA authors who are shaped by the journeys they and their families have taken from home—and to find home. WELCOME From some of the most exciting bestselling and up-and-coming YA authors writing today…journey from Ecuador to New York City and Argentina to Utah…from Australia to Harlem and India to New Jersey…from Fiji, America, Mexico and more… Come On In. With characters who face random traffic stops, TSA detention, customs anxiety, and the daunting and inspiring journey to new lands…who camp with their extended families, dance at weddings, keep diaries, teach ESL…who give up their rooms for displaced family, decide their own answer to the question “where are you from?” and so much more… Come On In illuminates fifteen of the myriad facets of the immigrant experience, from authors who have been shaped by the journeys they and their families have taken from home—and to find home.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-10-13\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.1.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fUi7DwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781488069383\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1488069387\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"kHGbDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"cyQwq3eLbEI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/kHGbDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=kHGbDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Told in Reyna’s exquisite, heartfelt prose, A Dream Called Home demonstrates how, by daring to pursue her dreams, Reyna was able to build the one thing she had always longed for: a home that would endure.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"A Dream Called Home\", \"authors\": [\"Reyna Grande\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=kHGbDwAAQBAJ&dq=college&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Memoir\", \"pageCount\": 336, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Washington Square Press\", \"categories\": [\"Biography & Autobiography\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kHGbDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kHGbDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"From bestselling author of the remarkable memoir, The Distance Between Us comes an inspiring account of one woman’s quest to find her place in America as a first-generation Latina university student and aspiring writer determined to build a new life for her family one fearless word at a time. “Here is a life story so unbelievable, it could only be true” (Sandra Cisneros, bestselling author of The House on Mango Street). As an immigrant in an unfamiliar country, with an indifferent mother and abusive father, Reyna had few resources at her disposal. Taking refuge in words, Reyna’s love of reading and writing propels her to rise above until she achieves the impossible and is accepted to the University of California, Santa Cruz. Although her acceptance is a triumph, the actual experience of American college life is intimidating and unfamiliar for someone like Reyna, who is now estranged from her family and support system. Again, she finds solace in words, holding fast to her vision of becoming a writer, only to discover she knows nothing about what it takes to make a career out of a dream. Through it all, Reyna is determined to make the impossible possible, going from undocumented immigrant of little means to “a fierce, smart, shimmering light of a writer” (Cheryl Strayed, author of Wild); a National Book Critics Circle Award Finalist whose “power is growing with every book” (Luis Alberto Urrea, Pultizer Prize finalist); and a proud mother of two beautiful children who will never have to know the pain of poverty and neglect. Told in Reyna’s exquisite, heartfelt prose, A Dream Called Home demonstrates how, by daring to pursue her dreams, Reyna was able to build the one thing she had always longed for: a home that would endure.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=kHGbDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 2, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 4.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2019-07-02\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.1.0.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/A_Dream_Called_Home.html?hl=&id=kHGbDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781501171437\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1501171437\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"C9GQMwEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"RKbmTOkDlLk\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/C9GQMwEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=C9GQMwEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This text blends traditional introductory physics topics with an emphasis on human applications and an expanded coverage of modern physics topics, such as the existence of atoms and the conversion of mass into energy.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"College Physics\", \"authors\": [\"Paul Peter Urone\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=C9GQMwEACAAJ&dq=college&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 893, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Brooks/Cole Publishing Company\", \"categories\": [\"Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=C9GQMwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=C9GQMwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This text blends traditional introductory physics topics with an emphasis on human applications and an expanded coverage of modern physics topics, such as the existence of atoms and the conversion of mass into energy. Topical coverage is combined with the author\'s lively, conversational writing style, innovative features, the direct and clear manner of presentation, and the emphasis on problem solving and practical applications.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=C9GQMwEACAAJ&dq=college&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 1, \"publishedDate\": \"1998-01-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/College_Physics.html?hl=&id=C9GQMwEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0534356044\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780534356040\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"qzWdDQAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"+iptuL67lJI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 27500000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 18250000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-qzWdDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 27.5, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 18.25, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/qzWdDQAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Trans_in_College-sample-pdf.acsm?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Trans_in_College-sample-epub.acsm?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"WINNER of 2017 AERA DIVISION J OUTSTANDING PUBLICATION AWARD CHOICE 2017 Outstanding Academic Title This is both a personal book that offers an account of the author’s own trans* identity and a deeply engaged study of trans* collegians ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Trans* in College\", \"authors\": [\"Z Nicolazzo\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Transgender Students\' Strategies for Navigating Campus Life and the Institutional Politics of Inclusion\", \"pageCount\": 232, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Stylus Publishing, LLC\", \"categories\": [\"Education\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"WINNER of 2017 AERA DIVISION J OUTSTANDING PUBLICATION AWARD This is both a personal book that offers an account of the author’s own trans* identity and a deeply engaged study of trans* collegians that reveals the complexities of trans* identities, and how these students navigate the trans* oppression present throughout society and their institutions, create community and resilience, and establish meaning and control in a world that assumes binary genders. This book is addressed as much to trans* students themselves – offering them a frame to understand the genders that mark them as different and to address the feelings brought on by the weight of that difference – as it is to faculty, student affairs professionals, and college administrators, opening up the implications for the classroom and the wider campus. This book not only remedies the paucity of literature on trans* college students, but does so from a perspective of resiliency and agency. Rather than situating trans* students as problems requiring accommodation, this book problematizes the college environment and frames trans* students as resilient individuals capable of participating in supportive communities and kinship networks, and of developing strategies to promote their own success. Z Nicolazzo provides the reader with a nuanced and illuminating review of the literature on gender and sexuality that sheds light on the multiplicity of potential expressions and outward representations of trans* identity as a prelude to the ethnography ze conducted with nine trans* collegians that richly documents their interactions with, and responses to, environments ranging from the unwittingly offensive to explicitly antagonistic. The book concludes by giving space to the study’s participants to themselves share what they want college faculty, staff, and students to know about their lived experiences. Two appendices respectively provide a glossary of vocabulary and terms to address commonly asked questions, and a description of the study design, offered as guide for others considering working alongside marginalized population in a manner that foregrounds ethics, care, and reciprocity.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2016-11-29\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.4.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qzWdDQAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781620364581\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1620364581\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"D9E1RE-BM2cC\", \"etag\": \"eAtCJeWZQlA\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 16950000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 16950000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&rdid=book-D9E1RE-BM2cC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 16.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 16.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/D9E1RE-BM2cC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Head_Off_Split-sample-pdf.acsm?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This is poetry to give thanks for.&quot;---Meena Alexander, author of Quickly Changing River &quot;No one opens a vein on the page with a sharper and more nuanced gathered set of senses than Nikky Finney.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Head Off & Split\", \"authors\": [\"Nikky Finney\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Poems\", \"pageCount\": 97, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Northwestern University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Poetry\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"\\\"Nikky Finney has been a fine poet much too long to say that this latest treasure is her promise coming into being. She exploded with so much talent with On Wings Made of Gauze and beautifully matured with Rice, yet Head Off & Split takes the promise of youth with the control of adulthood to bring her greatest exploration. Honest, searing, searching. We all, especially now, need this book of poems; we all, especially now, need this poet.\\\"---Nikki Giovanni, author of Bicycles \\\"Beginning with the sweepingly inclusive and powerful `Red Velvet,\' a Middle Passage poem for our times, Nikky Finney takes the reader to a wonderfully alive world where the musical possibilities of language overflow with surprise and innovation. Finney has an ear to go along with the wildness of her imagination, which sweeps through history like a pair of wings. Her carefully modulated free verse is always purposeful in its desire to move the reader in a way that allows us intimate access to necessary observations about ourselves. These poems, in other words, have the power to save us.\\\"---Bruce Weigl, author of What Saves Us \\\"In Nikky Finney\'s Head Off & Split the beauty of language soars and saves us even as we skirt the raw edge of terror. And something rare and precious is restored, a light, a circling movement of the spirit. This is poetry to give thanks for.\\\"---Meena Alexander, author of Quickly Changing River \\\"No one opens a vein on the page with a sharper and more nuanced gathered set of senses than Nikky Finney. In Head Off & Split, she takes aim at the heart of American wrong-headedness with a sense of purpose and integrity not only respectful of, but fueled by, her own brand of multiple kinships and remembrance, a grand struggle-swagger of powerful literary inheritance.\\\"---Thomas Sayers Ellis, author of Skin, Inc. \\\"With Head Off & Split, Nikky Finney establishes herself as one of the most eloquent, urgent, fearless and necessary poets writing in America today. What makes this book as important as anything published in the last decade is the irresistible music, the formal dexterity and the imaginative leaps she makes with metaphor and language in these simply stunning poems. This is a very, very important achievement.\\\"---Kwame Dawes, author of Hope\'s Hospice\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2011-01-27\", \"contentVersion\": \"2.1.1.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=D9E1RE-BM2cC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780810152168\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0810152169\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"doivSgAACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"BVof+inRazE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/doivSgAACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=doivSgAACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This book offers counselors an action-based curriculum that will meet the needs of the 21st century high school student, help to foster their growth and ambition, and engage them as constructivists in learning what they need to succeed ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Counseling 21st Century Students for Optimal College and Career Readiness\", \"authors\": [\"Corine Fitzpatrick\", \"Kathleen Costantini\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=doivSgAACAAJ&dq=college&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A 9th-12th Grade Curriculum\", \"pageCount\": 244, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"categories\": [\"Psychology\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=doivSgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=doivSgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"In order for students to compete in today\'s global economy, our schools need to help them develop better cognitive and technological skills. School counselors have an enormous impact on students\' achievement and their success in their post-secondary education, yet initiatives to improve student outcomes often overlook them. Fitzpatrick and Costantini present their own action-based curriculum for high school counselors that will meet the needs of 21st century students, helping to foster their growth and ambition and actively engage them in learning what they need to succeed beyond high school. Important steps covered in this curriculum include Making the transition to ninth grade successful Using technology in the advising process, such as online resources for college and career research, assessing interests, and structuring advising sessions Preparing for standardized testing and using it to motivate students about the college application process Assisting students in researching careers and colleges, making the most of college visits, applying for college, and writing the application essay Equally important, the book focuses on the counselor and his or her role as an advocate and leader for students and details running a guidance office, working with parents, and writing Secondary School Reports. While applicable for all school counselors and students, the authors\' curriculum has a special focus on students in urban public schools to enable them to have the same experiences as their counterparts in suburban and private schools. An accompanying CD contains the tables, exercises, and charts from the book so they can be easily accessed and reproduced.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=doivSgAACAAJ&dq=college&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2011\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Counseling_21st_Century_Students_for_Opt.html?hl=&id=doivSgAACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0415876125\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780415876124\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"3bG6vfiCnDsC\", \"etag\": \"fVJG8dX9NNM\", \"kind\": \"books#volu