dge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"For many college students, Spring Break means fun and sun in Florida. For Danny, a Yale junior, it means two weeks behind the wheel of the Roach Coach, his father\'s lunch truck, which plies the parking lots of office parks in central New Jersey. But Danny can use the time behind the coffee urn to try and make sense of a love life that\'s gotten a little complicated. There\'s loyal and patient hometown honey Cindy and her recently dropped bombshell to contend with. And there\'s also lissome Polly back in New Haven--with her shifting moods, perfect thrift store dresses and inconvenient liaison with a dashing professor. If girl problems aren\'t enough, there\'s the constant menace of the Lunch Monsters, a group of thugs who think Danny has planted the Roach Coach in their territory. Joe College is Tom Perrotta\'s warmest and funniest fiction yet, a comic journey into the dark side of love, higher education and food service.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=3bG6vfiCnDsC&printsec=frontcover&dq=college&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 8, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3, \"publishedDate\": \"2006-09-19\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.9.3.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3bG6vfiCnDsC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781429907804\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1429907800\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"l7XJAQAACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"zE3JOEGuU20\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/l7XJAQAACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=l7XJAQAACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"And it takes place before college, in college, after college, and without college. This is the wild, painful, awkward, hilarious, depressing, &amp; beautiful journey from youth to maturity. This is the college book that no one ever gave us.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"That College Book\", \"authors\": [\"Timothy Snyder\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=l7XJAQAACAAJ&dq=college&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Everything Nobody Told Us about Life After High School\", \"pageCount\": 172, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Createspace Independent Publishing Platform\", \"categories\": [\"College student orientation\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=l7XJAQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=l7XJAQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"In high school, everyone\'s talking about college. What to do. Where to go. Why it\'s important. Classes are given on it. Books are written about it. But details get left out. Every year, college graduates learn this the hard way as they step into adulthood. I was one of them. After earning a four-year degree, I went through two of the worst years of my life. Not that my situation is unique. I am a part of a generation that was told to go to college first and sort out the details later. Most of us did. We chased the promise of a big shiny future, and we ended up being chased by the mistakes of our past. That\'s not to say we completely regretted going. This book isn\'t a list of privileged millennial complaints. It\'s a collection of wisdom gained in less than pleasant ways. It\'s a story of hardship, failure, victory, and perseverance. It\'s all of the things we wish someone had told us. And it takes place before college, in college, after college, and without college. This is the wild, painful, awkward, hilarious, depressing, & beautiful journey from youth to maturity. This is the college book that no one ever gave us.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=l7XJAQAACAAJ&dq=college&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2017-03-13\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/That_College_Book.html?hl=&id=l7XJAQAACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1535243554\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781535243551\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 3031}'),('danger','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"uAsachI9SP4C\", \"etag\": \"3denMEZah/w\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/uAsachI9SP4C\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Lady_Danger-sample-epub.acsm?id=uAsachI9SP4C&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=uAsachI9SP4C&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Raised to fear no man, Deirdre of Rivenloch never backs down from a clash of steel or a threat to her lands and family.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Lady Danger\", \"authors\": [\"Sarah McKerrigan\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=uAsachI9SP4C&dq=danger&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 368, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Forever\", \"categories\": [\"Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uAsachI9SP4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uAsachI9SP4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Raised to fear no man, Deirdre of Rivenloch never backs down from a clash of steel or a threat to her lands and family. But when she tricks Sir Pagan Cameliard into marrying her in order to save her younger sister, she\'s faced with a new kind of enemy: a husband who would turn her resistance into a fire that heats her blood...and who would use all his cunning to make her cry his name in ultimate abandon. For Pagan has made his own wedding vow. he will best his sword-wielding bride in the field by day and make hersurrender in his arms by night. Her heart will be his.. even if it means being conquered by hers.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=uAsachI9SP4C&printsec=frontcover&dq=danger&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 2, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"2008-12-21\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.1.2.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Lady_Danger.html?hl=&id=uAsachI9SP4C\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780446555272\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0446555274\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"a3GrCgAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"eB7GIiw6aiE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/a3GrCgAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Spaces_of_Danger-sample-pdf.acsm?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Spaces_of_Danger-sample-epub.acsm?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The regimes of truth and systems of power sustaining such <b>dangers</b> were silenced, and the focus was on a single social anomaly—the madman. By characterizing Breivik as an evil aberration and abstracting his acts from the social and&nbsp;...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Spaces of Danger\", \"authors\": [\"Heather Merrill\", \"Lisa M. Hoffman\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&dq=danger&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Culture and Power in the Everyday\", \"pageCount\": 320, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Georgia Press\", \"categories\": [\"Social Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"These twelve original essays by geographers and anthropologists offer a deep critical understanding of Allan Pred’s pathbreaking and eclectic cultural Marxist approach, with a focus on his concept of “situated ignorance”: the production and reproduction of power and inequality by regimes of truth through strategically deployed misinformation, diversions, and silences. As the essays expose the cultural and material circumstances in which situated ignorance persists, they also add a previously underexplored spatial dimension to Walter Benjamin’s idea of “moments of danger.” The volume invokes the aftermath of the July 2011 attacks by far-right activist Anders Breivik in Norway, who ambushed a Labor Party youth gathering and bombed a government building, killing and injuring many. Breivik had publicly and forthrightly declared war against an array of liberal attitudes he saw threatening Western civilization. However, as politicians and journalists interpreted these events for mass consumption, a narrative quickly emerged that painted Breivik as a lone madman and steered the discourse away from analysis of the resurgent right-wing racisms and nationalisms in which he was immersed. The Breivik case is merely one of the most visible recent examples, say editors Heather Merrill and Lisa Hoffman, of the unchallenged production of knowledge in the public sphere. In essays that range widely in topic and setting—for example, brownfield development in China, a Holocaust memorial in Germany, an art gallery exhibit in South Africa—this volume peels back layers of “situated practices and their associated meaning and power relations.” Spaces of Danger offers analytical and conceptual tools of a Predian approach to interrogate the taken-for-granted and make visible and legible that which is silenced.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA2&dq=danger&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2015-12-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.2.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Spaces_of_Danger.html?hl=&id=a3GrCgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780820348766\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0820348767\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"fEKjJtPp_h8C\", \"etag\": \"AnhqImJZsW4\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/fEKjJtPp_h8C\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Extreme_Danger-sample-pdf.acsm?id=fEKjJtPp_h8C&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=fEKjJtPp_h8C&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"A <b>dangerous</b> state of affairs , for both of them . She must not glom onto this guy , make him her reason to exist . The <b>danger</b> was there . As sexy and charismatic as he was , as scared and vulnerable as she felt .\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Extreme Danger\", \"authors\": [\"Shannon McKenna\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=fEKjJtPp_h8C&dq=danger&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 432, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Brava