vid Shannon\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=YOHACwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 32, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Scholastic Inc.\", \"categories\": [\"Juvenile Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YOHACwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YOHACwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"When David Shannon was five years old, he wrote and illustrated his first book. On every page were these words: NO, DAVID! . . . and a picture of David doing things he was not supposed to do. Now David is all grown up. But some things never change. . . . Over fifteen years after its initial publication, NO, DAVID! remains a perennial household favorite, delighting children, parents, and teachers alike. David is a beloved character, whose unabashed good humor, mischievous smile, and laughter-inducing antics underline the love parents have for their children--even when they misbehave.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=YOHACwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=david&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 165, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2016-08-30\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.17.14.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=YOHACwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781338113198\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1338113194\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"-1JmBAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"Ht571iGnqJc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\