om=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-1JmBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Of all the figures in the Bible, David arguably stands out as the most perplexing and enigmatic. He was many things: a warrior who subdued Goliath and the Philistines; a king who united a nation; a poet who created beautiful, sensitive verse; a loyal servant of God who proposed the great Temple and founded the Messianic line; a schemer, deceiver, and adulterer who freely indulged his very human appetites. David Wolpe, whom Newsweek called “the most influential rabbi in America,” takes a fresh look at biblical David in an attempt to find coherence in his seemingly contradictory actions and impulses. The author questions why David holds such an exalted place in history and legend, and then proceeds to unravel his complex character based on information found in the book of Samuel and later literature. What emerges is a fascinating portrait of an exceptional human being who, despite his many flaws, was truly beloved by God.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=-1JmBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=david&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2014-09-16\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.2.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-1JmBAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780300210163\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0300210167\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"Xq1LnwEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"UCF01y72Tdg\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/Xq1LnwEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=Xq1LnwEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Even as a toddler, David was a challenge to his parents.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Oh, David!\", \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Xq1LnwEACAAJ&dq=david&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 12, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Blue Sky Press (AZ)\", \"categories\": [\"Juvenile Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Xq1LnwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Xq1LnwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Even as a toddler, David was a challenge to his parents.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Xq1LnwEACAAJ&dq=david&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2005\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Oh_David.html?hl=&id=Xq1LnwEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0439688817\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780439688819\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"TEwVdltjBSQC\", \"etag\": \"elxxxZrxF14\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&rdid=book-TEwVdltjBSQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/TEwVdltjBSQC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/King_David-sample-pdf.acsm?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/King_David-sample-epub.acsm?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Now, in King David: The Real Life of the Man Who Ruled Israel, bestselling author Jonathan Kirsch reveals this commanding individual in all his glory and fallibility.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"King David\", \"authors\": [\"Jonathan Kirsch\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Real Life of the Man Who Ruled Israel\", \"pageCount\": 400, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Ballantine Books\", \"categories\": [\"Biography & Autobiography\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"David, King of the Jews, possessed every flaw and failing a mortal is capable of, yet men and women adored him and God showered him with many more blessings than he did Abraham or Moses. His sexual appetite and prowess were matched only by his violence, both on the battlefield and in the bedroom. A charismatic leader, exalted as \\\"a man after God\'s own heart,\\\" he was also capable of deep cunning, deceit, and betrayal. Now, in King David: The Real Life of the Man Who Ruled Israel, bestselling author Jonathan Kirsch reveals this commanding individual in all his glory and fallibility. In a taut, dramatic narrative, Kirsch brings new depth and psychological complexity to the familiar events of David\'s life--his slaying of the giant Goliath and his swift challenge to the weak rule of Saul, the first Jewish king; his tragic relationship with Saul\'s son Jonathan, David\'s cherished friend (and possibly lover); his celebrated reign in Jerusalem, where his dynasty would hold sway for generations. Yet for all his greatness, David was also a man in thrall to his passions--a voracious lover who secured the favors of his beautiful mistress Bathsheba by secretly arranging the death of her innocent husband; a merciless warrior who triumphed through cruelty; a troubled father who failed to protect his daughter from rape and whose beloved son Absalom rose against him in armed insurrection. Weaving together biblical texts with centuries of interpretation and commentary, Jonathan Kirsch brings King David to life in these pages with extraordinary freshness, intimacy, and vividness of detail. At the center of this inspiring narrative stands a hero of flesh and blood--not the cartoon giant-slayer of sermons and Sunday school stories or the immaculate ruler of legend and art but a magnetic, disturbingly familiar man--a man as vibrant and compelling today as he has been for millennia.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=TEwVdltjBSQC&printsec=frontcover&dq=david&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 3, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 3, \"publishedDate\": \"2009-07-22\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.6.3.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=TEwVdltjBSQC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780307567819\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0307567818\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"4xkcFXVZ5zgC\", \"etag\": \"ZGrh1nW4fcI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 18950000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 9990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&rdid=book-4xkcFXVZ5zgC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 18.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 9.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/4xkcFXVZ5zgC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_David_Story_A_Translation_with_Comme-sample-epub.acsm?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"&quot;A masterpiece of contemporary Bible translation and commentary.&quot;—Los Angeles Times Book Review, Best Books of 1999 Acclaimed for its masterful new translation and insightful commentary, The David Story is a fresh, vivid rendition of one ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The David Story: A Translation with Commentary of 1 and 2 Samuel\", \"authors\": [\"Robert Alter\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 448, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"W. W. Norton & Company\", \"categories\": [\"Religion\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"\\\"A masterpiece of contemporary Bible translation and commentary.\\\"—Los Angeles Times Book Review, Best Books of 1999 Acclaimed for its masterful new translation and insightful commentary, The David Story is a fresh, vivid rendition of one of the great works in Western literature. Robert Alter\'s brilliant translation gives us David, the beautiful, musical hero who slays Goliath and, through his struggles with Saul, advances to the kingship of Israel. But this David is also fully human: an ambitious, calculating man who navigates his life\'s course with a flawed moral vision. The consequences for him, his family, and his nation are tragic and bloody. Historical personage and full-blooded imagining, David is the creation of a literary artist comparable to the Shakespeare of the history plays.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=4xkcFXVZ5zgC&printsec=frontcover&dq=david&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 7, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 4.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2009-10-21\"