le-pdf.acsm?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Science_of_Dune-sample-epub.acsm?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This guide offers fascinating scientific speculation on topics including quantum physics, biochemistry, ecology, evolution, psychology, technology, and genetics.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Science of Dune\", \"authors\": [\"Kevin R. Grazier\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"An Unauthorized Exploration into the Real Science Behind Frank Herbert\'s Fictional Universe\", \"pageCount\": 232, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"BenBella Books, Inc.\", \"categories\": [\"Social Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Could sandworms really exist? What’s in that mélange, anyway? The Science of Dune provides the answers to these questions... and many more! Since its original publication in 1965, the Dune series has entranced generations of readers with its complex plotting, fascinating characters, grand scope, and incredible scientific predictions. This guide offers fascinating scientific speculation on topics including quantum physics, biochemistry, ecology, evolution, psychology, technology, and genetics. It scrutinizes Frank Herbert’s science fiction world by asking questions such as: Is the ecology of Dune realistic? Is it theoretically possible to get information from the future? Could humans really evolve as Herbert suggests? Which of Herbert’s inventions have already come to life? This companion is a must-have for any fan who wants to revisit the world of Dune and explore it even further.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=4kbYExSCa6oC&printsec=frontcover&dq=dune&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2007-12-11\", \"contentVersion\": \"3.5.5.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4kbYExSCa6oC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781935251408\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1935251406\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"GkYFzgEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"hLiewul9APE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/GkYFzgEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=GkYFzgEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The Duke of Atreides has been manoeuvred by his arch-enemy, Baron Harkonnen, into administering the desert planet of Dune.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Dune\", \"authors\": [\"Frank Herbert\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=GkYFzgEACAAJ&dq=dune&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Now a Major New Film from the Director of Blade Runner 2049\", \"pageCount\": 624, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Gollancz\", \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GkYFzgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GkYFzgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=GkYFzgEACAAJ&dq=dune&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-09-02\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Dune.html?hl=&id=GkYFzgEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"147323395X\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781473233959\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"sqrpDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"qohu02xEFEg\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/sqrpDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=sqrpDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Set on the desert planet Arrakis, Dune is the story of the boy Paul Atreides, heir to a noble family tasked with ruling an inhospitable world where the only thing of value is the “spice” melange, a drug capable of extending life and ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Dune (Movie Tie-In)\", \"authors\": [\"Frank Herbert\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=sqrpDwAAQBAJ&dq=dune&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 896, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Penguin\", \"categories\": [\"Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sqrpDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sqrpDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"SOON TO BE A MAJOR MOTION PICTURE directed by Denis Villeneuve, starring Timothée Chalamet, Josh Brolin, Jason Momoa, Zendaya, Rebecca Ferguson, Oscar Isaac, Javier Bardem, Dave Bautista, Stellan Skarsgård, and Charlotte Rampling. Frank Herbert’s classic masterpiece—a triumph of the imagination and one of the bestselling science fiction novels of all time. Set on the desert planet Arrakis, Dune is the story of the boy Paul Atreides, heir to a noble family tasked with ruling an inhospitable world where the only thing of value is the “spice” melange, a drug capable of extending life and enhancing consciousness. Coveted across the known universe, melange is a prize worth killing for.... When House Atreides is betrayed, the destruction of Paul’s family will set the boy on a journey toward a destiny greater than he could ever have imagined. And as he evolves into the mysterious man known as Muad’Dib, he will bring to fruition humankind’s most ancient and unattainable dream. A stunning blend of adventure and mysticism, environmentalism and politics, Dune won the first Nebula Award, shared the Hugo Award, and formed the basis of what is undoubtedly the grandest epic in science fiction.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=sqrpDwAAQBAJ&dq=dune&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2020\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Dune_Movie_Tie_In.html?hl=&id=sqrpDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780593334713\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"059333471X\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"9QYJe3eEbu0C\", \"etag\": \"7Vd2Q8nRXz0\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/9QYJe3eEbu0C\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Dune_and_Philosophy-sample-pdf.acsm?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Dune_and_Philosophy-sample-epub.acsm?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Frank Herbert&#39;s Dune is the biggest-selling science fiction story of all time; the original book and its numerous sequels have transported millions of readers into the alternate reality of the Duniverse.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Dune and Philosophy\", \"authors\": [\"Jeffery Nicholas\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&dq=dune&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Weirding Way of the Mentat\", \"pageCount\": 235, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Open Court Publishing\", \"categories\": [\"Literary Criticism\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Frank Herbert\'sDune is the biggest-selling science fiction story of all time; the original book and its numerous sequels have transported millions of readers into the alternate reality of the Duniverse.Dune and Philosophy raises intriguing questions about the Duniverse in ways that will be instantly meaningful to fans. Those well-known characters--Paul Atreides, Baron Harkkonen, Duncan Idaho, Stilgar, the Bene Gesserit witches--come alive again in this fearless philosophical probing of some of life\'s most basic questions. Dune presents us with a vast world in which fanaticism is merciless and history is made by the interplay of ruthless conspiracies. Computers have long been outlawed, so that the abilities of human beings are developed to an almost supernatural level. The intergalactic empire controlled by a privileged aristocracy raises all the old questions of human interaction in a strange yet weirdly familiar setting. Do secret conspiracies direct the future course of human political evolution? Can manipulation of the gene pool create a godlike individual? Are strife and bloodshed essential to progress? Can we know so much about the future that we lose the power to make a difference? Does reliance on valuable resources--such as \\\"spice,\\\" oil, and water--place us at the mercy of those who can destroy those resources? When gholas are reconstructed from the cells of dead people and given those people\'s memories, is the ghola the dead person resurrected? Can the exploitation of religion for political ends be reduced to a technique? Philosophers who are fans ofDune will trek through the desert of the Duniverse seeing answers to these and other questions.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=9QYJe3eEbu0C&printsec=frontcover&dq=dune&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2011\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.5.7.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Dune_and_Philosophy.html?hl=&id=9QYJe3eEbu0C\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780812697155\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0812697154\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"hkYnTJ6KWpcC\", \"etag\": \"5t6fL+DHbUU\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/hkYnTJ6KWpcC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=hkYnTJ6KWpcC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Praise for &quot;Dune: The Butlerian Jihad &quot;&quot;The kind of intricate plotting and philosophical musings that would make the elder Herbert proud.Throughout, key revelations regarding the Zensunni Wanderers and their fight for freedom and other ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Dune: The Machine Crusade\", \"authors\": [\"Brian Herbert\", \"Kevin J. Anderson\", \"Frank Herbert\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=hkYnTJ6KWpcC&dq=dune&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 701, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Macmillan\", \"categories\": [\"Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hkYnTJ6KWpcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hkYnTJ6KWpcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"As the struggle against the thinking robots continues, Serena Butler\'s forces continue their battle, the Cymeks scheme to regain their lost power from Omnius, Aurelius Venport and Norma Cenva are on the verge of a seminal scientific discovery, and Selim Wormrider and his Fremen outlaws take the first step into becoming the fighters who would change history. 250,000 first printing.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=hkYnTJ6KWpcC&printsec=frontcover&dq=dune&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2003-09-16\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.1.1.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Dune_The_Machine_Crusade.html?hl=&id=hkYnTJ6KWpcC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780765301581\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"076530158X\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"aQ9UEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"XIM+/98uHe0\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/aQ9UEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=aQ9UEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The Art and Soul of Dune also features exclusive interviews with key members of the cast and crew, including Denis Villeneuve, Timothée Chalamet, Rebecca Ferguson, Oscar Isaac, and many more, delivering a uniquely candid account of the ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Art and Soul of Dune\", \"authors\": [\"Tanya Lapointe\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=aQ9UEAAAQBAJ&dq=dune&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 240, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Simon and Schuster\", \"categories\": [\"Art\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aQ9UEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aQ9UEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Immerse yourself in the world of Denis Villeneuve’s Dune and discover the incredible creative journey that brought Frank Herbert’s iconic novel to the big screen. Frank Herbert’s science fiction classic Dune has been brought to life like never before in the breathtaking film adaptation from acclaimed director Denis Villeneuve (Blade Runner 2049, Arrival). Now fans can be part of this creative journey with The Art and Soul of Dune, the official companion to the hugely anticipated movie event. Written by Dune executive producer Tanya Lapointe, this visually dazzling exploration of the filmmaking process gives unparalleled insight into the project’s genesis—from its striking environmental and creature designs to its intricate costume concepts and landmark digital effects. The Art and Soul of Dune also features exclusive interviews with key members of the cast and crew, including Denis Villeneuve, Timothée Chalamet, Rebecca Ferguson, Oscar Isaac, and many more, delivering a uniquely candid account of the hugely ambitious international shoot. Showcasing Villeneuve’s visionary approach to realizing Herbert’s science fiction classic, The Art and Soul of Dune is an essential companion to the director’s latest masterpiece.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=aQ9UEAAAQBAJ&pg=PA1&dq=dune&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-10-22\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.1.0.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Art_and_Soul_of_Dune.html?hl=&id=aQ9UEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781647221553\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1647221552\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"AKOVzQEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"fQNQ9WozzOc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/AKOVzQEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=AKOVzQEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"&quot;En el desértico planeta Arrakis, el agua es el bien más preciado y llorar a los muertos, el símbolo de máxima prodigalidad.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Dune (Spanish Edition)\", \"authors\": [\"Herbert Frank\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=AKOVzQEACAAJ&dq=dune&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"es\", \"pageCount\": 256, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Salamandra Bolsillo\", \"categories\": [\"Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AKOVzQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AKOVzQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"En el desértico planeta Arrakis, el agua es el bien más preciado y llorar a los muertos, el símbolo de máxima prodigalidad. Pero algo hace de Arrakis una pieza estratégica para los intereses del emperador, las Grandes Casas y la Cofradía, los tres grandes poderes de la galaxia. Arrakis es el único origen conocido de la melange, preciosa especia y uno de los bienes más codiciados del universo. Al duque Leto Atreides se le asigna el gobierno de este mundo inhóspito, habitado por los indómitos Fremen y por monstruosos gusanos de arena de centenares de metros de longitud. Sin embargo, cuando la familia es traicionada, su hijo y heredero, Paul, emprenderá un viaje hacia un destino más grande del que jamás hubiese podido soñar. Mezcla fascinante de aventura, misticismo, intrigas políticas y ecologismo, Dune se convirtió, desde el momento de su publicación, en un fenómeno de culto y en la mayor epopeya de ciencia ficción de todos los tiempos. «No conozco nada comparable, excepto El Señor de los Anillos.» -Arthur C. Clarke ENGLISH DESCRIPTION Frank Herbert\'s classic masterpiece--a triumph of the imagination and one of the bestselling science fiction novels of all time. Set on the desert planet Arrakis, Dune is the story of the boy Paul Atreides, heir to a noble family tasked with ruling an inhospitable world where the only thing of value is the \\\"spice\\\" melange, a drug capable of extending life and enhancing consciousness. Coveted across the known universe, melange is a prize worth killing for.... When House Atreides is betrayed, the destruction of Paul\'s family will set the boy on a journey toward a destiny greater than he could ever have imagined. And as he evolves into the mysterious man known as Muad\'Dib, he will bring to fruition humankind\'s most ancient and unattainable dream. A stunning blend of adventure and mysticism, environmentalism and politics, Dune won the first Nebula Award, shared the Hugo Award, and formed the basis of what is undoubtedly the grandest epic in science fiction.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=AKOVzQEACAAJ&dq=dune&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-11-17\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Dune_Spanish_Edition.html?hl=&id=AKOVzQEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"6073194641\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9786073194648\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 2194}'),('fashion','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"3jBzzgEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"FAoP5+PxMHE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/3jBzzgEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=3jBzzgEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The first-ever authoritative A-Z celebration of the 500 greatest names in men&#39;s fas