tseller The Fashion Book takes a ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Fashion Book\", \"authors\": [\"Phaidon Editors\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=vNzLyQEACAAJ&dq=fashion&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 584, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Phaidon Press\", \"categories\": [\"Photography\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vNzLyQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vNzLyQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The iconic bestseller - showcasing more than 500 of fashion\'s greatest names by A- Z - now updated in a stunning new edition Fully revised and updated for 2020, this new edition of Phaidon\'s iconic global bestseller The Fashion Book takes a fresh look at the fashion world and the people who created and inspired it. Spanning almost 200 years, the entire industry is represented: from designers to photographers, stylists, and retailers, as well as editors and creative directors. Marking significant changes on the fashion landscape, this revised edition features important new names who have fundamentally shaped the way we see fashion in recent years, including Virgil Abloh, Gosha, and Alessandro Michele, influential image-maker Petra Collins, model and contemporary icon Rihanna, and Leandra Medine, alongside fashion pioneers of the previous edition such as Coco Chanel, Issey Miyake, Kate Moss, Erdem, and Richard Avedon. This bestselling - and now updated - classic volume remains a comprehensive and definitive view of the fashion industry today.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=vNzLyQEACAAJ&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-05-13\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Fashion_Book.html?hl=&id=vNzLyQEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1838661107\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781838661106\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"T6LTCgAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"25m3vF8dwGE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 36850000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 29110000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-T6LTCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 36.85, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 29.11, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/T6LTCgAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_First_Book_of_Fashion-sample-pdf.acsm?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_First_Book_of_Fashion-sample-epub.acsm?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This captivating book reproduces arguably the most extraordinary primary source documents in fashion history.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The First Book of Fashion\", \"authors\": [\"Ulinka Rublack\", \"Maria Hayward\", \"Jenny Tiramani\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Book of Clothes of Matthaeus and Veit Konrad Schwarz of Augsburg\", \"pageCount\": 432, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Bloomsbury Publishing\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This captivating book reproduces arguably the most extraordinary primary source documents in fashion history. Providing a revealing window onto the Renaissance, they chronicle how style-conscious accountant Matthäus Schwarz and his son Veit Konrad experienced life through clothes, and climbed the social ladder through fastidious management of self-image. These bourgeois dandies\' agenda resonates as powerfully today as it did in the sixteenth century: one has to dress to impress, and dress to impress they did. The Schwarzes recorded their sartorial triumphs as well as failures in life in a series of portraits by illuminists over 60 years, which have been comprehensively reproduced in full color for the first time. These exquisite illustrations are accompanied by the Schwarzes\' fashion-focussed yet at times deeply personal captions, which render the pair the world\'s first fashion bloggers and pioneers of everyday portraiture. The First Book of Fashion demonstrates how dress – seemingly both ephemeral and trivial – is a potent tool in the right hands. Beyond this, it colorfully recaptures the experience of Renaissance life and reveals the importance of clothing to the aesthetics and every day culture of the period. Historians Ulinka Rublack\'s and Maria Hayward\'s insightful commentaries create an unparalleled portrait of sixteenth-century dress that is both strikingly modern and thorough in its description of a true Renaissance fashionista\'s wardrobe. This first English translation also includes a bespoke pattern by TONY award-winning costume designer and dress historian Jenny Tiramani, from which readers can recreate one of Schwarz\'s most elaborate and politically significant outfits.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-02-11\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.5.4.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=T6LTCgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781474249904\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1474249906\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"mPP7RmSfkCEC\", \"etag\": \"WEVSJbeRZww\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/mPP7RmSfkCEC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=mPP7RmSfkCEC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Presents a decade-by-decade guide to the most influential looks of the past century, matching red-carpet gowns to famous celebrities while providing original designer sketches, photos of rare couture, and interviews with a range of ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Decades\", \"authors\": [\"Cameron Silver\", \"Rebecca DiLiberto\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=mPP7RmSfkCEC&dq=fashion&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Century of Fashion\", \"pageCount\": 247, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Bloomsbury Publishing USA\", \"categories\": [\"Design\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mPP7RmSfkCEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mPP7RmSfkCEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Presents a decade-by-decade guide to the most influential looks of the past century, matching red-carpet gowns to famous celebrities while providing original designer sketches, photos of rare couture, and interviews with a range of authorities.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=mPP7RmSfkCEC&printsec=frontcover&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"2012-10-16\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.4.0.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Decades.html?hl=&id=mPP7RmSfkCEC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781596916630\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"159691663X\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"p-KvoXTYtVoC\", \"etag\": \"BB1bd3bmS04\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/p-KvoXTYtVoC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Fashion_Culture_and_Identity-sample-epub.acsm?id=p-KvoXTYtVoC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=p-KvoXTYtVoC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Drawing on interviews with designers and fashion editors, Davis shows, in this provocative look at what we do with our clothes, how our ambivalent world reveals itself through fashion.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Fashion, Culture, and Identity\", \"authors\": [\"Fred Davis\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=p-KvoXTYtVoC&dq=fashion&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 226, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Chicago Press\", \"categories\": [\"Art\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p-KvoXTYtVoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p-KvoXTYtVoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Drawing on interviews with designers and fashion editors, Davis shows, in this provocative look at what we do with our clothes, how our ambivalent world reveals itself through fashion. He sets out to answer questions such as \'what do our clothes say about who we are or who we think we are?\', and \'how does the way we dress communicate messages about our identities?\', and demonstrates that much of what we assume to be individual preference really reflects deeper social and cultural forces, characterised by tensions over gender roles, social status and the expression of sexuality.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=p-KvoXTYtVoC&printsec=frontcover&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 4, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"1994-09\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.4.5.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Fashion_Culture_and_Identity.html?hl=&id=p-KvoXTYtVoC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0226138097\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780226138091\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"WFVOEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"hc4AmlsOrAc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/WFVOEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=WFVOEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This book features a wide array of fashion voices across the nation, who share self-generated images and narratives on how they define and identify with fashion now.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The United States of Fashion\", \"authors\": [\"THE EDITORS OF VOGUE\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=WFVOEAAAQBAJ&dq=fashion&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A New Atlas of American Style\", \"pageCount\": 176, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Rizzoli Publications\", \"categories\": [\"Design\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WFVOEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WFVOEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The editors of Vogue, the ultimate authority on fashion, document the post-COVID changes happening across the fashion landscape in America. Celebrating creators, artisans, and visionaries across the country, the book pays tribute to the democratization of American fashion and the creativity and artisanship that is no longer confined to the runways of New York and Los Angeles. In their February 2021 issue, Vogue launched “The United States of Fashion,” a project that shines a spotlight on the creativity and craft flourishing throughout the country. Exploring the innovation and entrepreneurialism that defines American fashion, Vogue goes coast to coast from Detroit to El Paso to Indianapolis to Nashville, where the most exciting new designers are creating and designing locally. This book features a wide array of fashion voices across the nation, who share self-generated images and narratives on how they define and identify with fashion now. New, never-before-seen photographs and anecdotes, not published in the pages of Vogue, come from fashion designers Laura and Kate Mulleavy of Rodarte, Jeremy Scott, and Libertine; photographers Alex Webb and June Canedo; and craftspeople Ariana Boussard-Reifel and Ataumbi Metals. The book contains texts by esteemed writers, from Louise Erdrich’s words on Native American fashion and music editor Suzy Exposito’s account of being goth in Miami, to new ways of creating sustainable, recycled fashion. These accounts create a living biography of the evolution and democratization of fashion today. A rich tapestry of style in America, The United States of Fashion will appeal to readers interested in fashion, design, culture, and photography.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=WFVOEAAAQBAJ&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-09-07\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_United_States_of_Fashion.html?hl=&id=WFVOEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780847871032\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0847871037\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"VT_r8GgEoKkC\", \"etag\": \"BOoifyWwGOc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 36990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 36990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}, {\"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 5550000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 4500000}, \"rentalDuration\": {\"unit\": \"HOUR\", \"count\": 24}, \"finskyOfferType\": 3}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&rdid=book-VT_r8GgEoKkC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 36.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 36.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE_AND_RENTAL\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/VT_r8GgEoKkC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Fashion_and_Its_Social_Agendas-sample-pdf.acsm?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Fashion_and_Its_Social_Agendas-sample-epub.acsm?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"An absorbing work, Fashion and Its Social Agendas stands out as a critical study of gender, fashion, and consumer culture. &quot;Why do people dress the way they do?\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Fashion and Its Social Agendas\", \"authors\": [\"Diana Crane\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Class, Gender, and Identity in Clothing\", \"pageCount\": 304, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Chicago Press\", \"categories\": [\"Social Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"It has long been said that clothes make the man (or woman), but is it still true today? If so, how has the information clothes convey changed over the years? Using a wide range of historical and contemporary materials, Diana Crane demonstrates how the social significance of clothing has been transformed. Crane compares nineteenth-century societies—France and the United States—where social class was the most salient aspect of social identity signified in clothing with late twentieth-century America, where lifestyle, gender, sexual orientation, age, and ethnicity are more meaningful to individuals in constructing their wardrobes. Today, clothes worn at work signify social class, but leisure clothes convey meanings ranging from trite to political. In today\'s multicode societies, clothes inhibit as well as facilitate communication between highly fragmented social groups. Crane extends her comparison by showing how nineteenth-century French designers created fashions that suited lifestyles of Paris elites but that were also widely adopted outside France. By contrast, today\'s designers operate in a global marketplace, shaped by television, film, and popular music. No longer confined to elites, trendsetters are drawn from many social groups, and most trends have short trajectories. To assess the impact of fashion on women, Crane uses voices of college-aged and middle-aged women who took part in focus groups. These discussions yield fascinating information about women\'s perceptions of female identity and sexuality in the fashion industry. An absorbing work, Fashion and Its Social Agendas stands out as a critical study of gender, fashion, and consumer culture. \\\"Why do people dress the way they do? How does clothing contribute to a person\'s identity as a man or woman, as a white-collar professional or blue-collar worker, as a preppie, yuppie, or nerd? How is it that dress no longer denotes social class so much as lifestyle? . . . Intelligent and informative, [this] book proposes thoughtful answers to some of these questions.\\\"-Library Journal\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC&printsec=frontcover&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 2, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 3.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2012-06-12\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.5.4.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=VT_r8GgEoKkC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780226924830\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0226924831\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"rAXeDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"HQkuJVtnG7c\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 19990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 19990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-rAXeDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 19.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 19.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/rAXeDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Fashion-sample-pdf.acsm?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Fashion-sample-epub.acsm?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Is fashion your passion? Unlock the language of clothes with this ultimate fashion show that traces people&#39;s dresses over the past 3000 years.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Fashion\", \"authors\": [\"DK\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Definitive Visual Guide\", \"pageCount\": 480, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Penguin\", \"categories\": [\"Design\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Is fashion your passion? Unlock the language of clothes with this ultimate fashion show that traces people\'s dresses over the past 3000 years. Fashion is a visual feast, packed with stunning illustrations of 1,500 costumes from around the globe. It celebrates famous trendsetters, designers, and fashion icons from Queen Henrietta Maria to Jackie Onassis and Jean Paul Gautier. Fashion endlessly reinvents itself, reflecting society\'s trends and innovations. Discover why different looks caught on, from the elaborate ruffs, wigs, and farthingales of the 17th century, to Dior\'s \\\"new look\\\" in 1947 and shoulder pads in the 1980s. Find out why for centuries people\'s dress was regulated by governments\' \\\"sumptuary rules\\\" and how the invention of new textiles from velvet to spandex that influenced clothing design. Whether you\'re part of the fashion industry, a student, or you just love clothes, Fashion is both a glorious visual treat and a treasured history.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA1&dq=fashion&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2019-09-03\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=rAXeDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780744022827\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0744022827\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 3023}'),('food','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"6pImDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"B5Kkr7vz40M\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 14990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 14990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6pImDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 14.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 14.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/6pImDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Food-sample-epub.acsm?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"#1 New York Times bestselling author Dr. Mark Hyman sorts through the conflicting research on food to give us the skinny on what to eat.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Food\", \"authors\": [\"Mark Hyman\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"What the Heck Should I Eat?\", \"pageCount\": 400, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Little, Brown\", \"categories\": [\"Health & Fitness\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"#1 New York Times bestselling author Dr. Mark Hyman sorts through the conflicting research on food to give us the skinny on what to eat. Did you know that eating oatmeal actually isn\'t a healthy way to start the day? That milk doesn\'t build bones, and eggs aren\'t the devil? Even the most health conscious among us have a hard time figuring out what to eat in order to lose weight, stay fit, and improve our health. And who can blame us? When it comes to diet, there\'s so much changing and conflicting information flying around that it\'s impossible to know where to look for sound advice. And decades of misguided \\\"common sense,\\\" food-industry lobbying, bad science, and corrupt food polices and guidelines have only deepened our crisis of nutritional confusion, leaving us overwhelmed and anxious when we head to the grocery store. Thankfully, bestselling author Dr. Mark Hyman is here to set the record straight. In Food: What the Heck Should I Eat? -- his most comprehensive book yet -- he takes a close look at every food group and explains what we\'ve gotten wrong, revealing which foods nurture our health and which pose a threat. From grains to legumes, meat to dairy, fats to artificial sweeteners, and beyond, Dr. Hyman debunks misconceptions and breaks down the fascinating science in his signature accessible style. He also explains food\'s role as powerful medicine capable of reversing chronic disease and shows how our food system and policies impact the environment, the economy, social justice, and personal health, painting a holistic picture of growing, cooking, and eating food in ways that nourish our bodies and the earth while creating a healthy society. With myth-busting insights, easy-to-understand science, and delicious, wholesome recipes, Food: What the Heck Should I Eat? is a no-nonsense guide to achieving optimal weight and lifelong health.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=6pImDwAAQBAJ&printsec=fro