peechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Moving from the local, the intimate, and the small to the national, the impersonal, and the large, this book&#39;s interpenetrating chapters show the unexpected social and political force of the ordinary in the production of memory.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"What Remains\", \"authors\": [\"Jonathan Bach\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=HMMtDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Everyday Encounters with the Socialist Past in Germany\", \"pageCount\": 200, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Columbia University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Social Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HMMtDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HMMtDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"What happens when an entire modern state\'s material culture becomes abruptly obsolete? How do ordinary people encounter what remains? In this ethnography, Jonathan Bach examines the afterlife of East Germany following the fall of the Berlin Wall, as things and places from that vanished socialist past continue to circulate and shape the politics of memory. What Remains traces the unsettling effects of these unmoored artifacts on the German present, arguing for a rethinking of the role of the everyday as a site of reckoning with difficult pasts. Bach juxtaposes four sites where the stakes of the everyday appear: products commodified as nostalgia, amateur museums dedicated to collecting everyday life under socialism, the \\\"people\'s palace\\\" that captured the national imagination through its destruction, and the feared and fetishized Berlin Wall. Moving from the local, the intimate, and the small to the national, the impersonal, and the large, this book\'s interpenetrating chapters show the unexpected social and political force of the ordinary in the production of memory. What Remains offers a unique vantage point on the workings of the everyday in situations of radical discontinuity, contributing to new understandings of postsocialism and the intricate intersection of material remains and memory.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=HMMtDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=germany&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2017-08-29\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.3.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=HMMtDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780231544306\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0231544308\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 3015}'),('ghandi','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"qN96JgiMlscC\", \"etag\": \"eLoJhHb4cuc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/qN96JgiMlscC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=qN96JgiMlscC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Originally published in 1965, a compendium of excerpts offers insight into the spiritual leader&#39;s beliefs about action as a central component of non-violent resistance, his opposition to the caste system, and legacy as a proponent of ...\"}