must go there. Working his way north over nearly a decade, Kpomassie finally arrived in the country of his dreams. This brilliantly observed and superbly entertaining record of his adventures among the Inuit is a testament both to the wonderful strangeness of the human species and to the surprising sympathies that bind us all.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=MiBOEAAAQBAJ&dq=greenland&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 12, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2001-10-31\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/An_African_in_Greenland.html?hl=&id=MiBOEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780940322882\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0940322889\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"LcNvDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"AQmxc/Qo9Vc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/LcNvDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=LcNvDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Maine to Greenland is a testament to one of the world&#39;s great geographic regions: the Maritime Far Northeast.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Maine to Greenland\", \"authors\": [\"Wilfred E. Richard\", \"William Fitzhugh\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=LcNvDwAAQBAJ&dq=greenland&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Exploring the Maritime Far Northeast\", \"pageCount\": 272, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Smithsonian Institution\", \"categories\": [\"Travel\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LcNvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LcNvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Maine to Greenland is a testament to one of the world\'s great geographic regions: the Maritime Far Northeast. For more than three decades, William W. Fitzhugh and Wilfred E. Richard have explored the Northeast’s Atlantic corridor and its fascinating history, habitat, and culture. The authors’ powerful personal essays and Richard’s stunning photography transport readers to this vibrant region, joining Smithsonian archaeological expeditions and trekking in vast and amazing terrain. Following Fitzhugh and Richard’s travels north—from Maine to the Canadian Maritimes, Newfoundland and northern Quebec, then to Labrador, Baffin and Ellesmere islands, and Greenland—we view incredible landscapes, uncover human history, and meet luminous personalities along the way. Fully illustrated with 350 full-color photographs, Maine to Greenland is the first in-depth treatment of the Northeast Atlantic corridor and essential for armchair travelers, locals, tourists, or anyone who has journeyed there. Today green technology, climate change, and the opening of the Arctic Ocean have transformed the Maritime Far Northeast from an icy frontier into a global resource zone and an increasingly integrated international crossroads. In our rapidly converging world, we have much to learn from the Maritime Far Northeast and how its variety of cultures have adapted to rather than changed their environments during the past ten thousand years. Maine to Greenland is not only a complete account of the region’s unique culture and environment, but also a timely reminder that amidst the very real consequences of climate change, the inhabitants of the Maritime Far Northeast can show us grounded and sustainable ways of living.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=LcNvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=greenland&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 3, \"publishedDate\": \"2014-08-05\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Maine_to_Greenland.html?hl=&id=LcNvDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781588343772\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1588343774\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"jzVcvTkgkYQC\", \"etag\": \"NszCaPrR1AQ\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jzVcvTkgkYQC&rdid=book-jzVcvTkgkYQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"saleability\": \"FREE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/jzVcvTkgkYQC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"downloadLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/A_Description_of_Greenland.pdf?id=jzVcvTkgkYQC&hl=&output=pdf&sig=ACfU3U2vo8T9eXZEELYJ3gylkLcuqvSe8Q&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false, \"downloadLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/A_Description_of_Greenland.epub?id=jzVcvTkgkYQC&hl=&output=epub&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"ALL_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": true, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=jzVcvTkgkYQC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"FULL_PUBLIC