&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=b1Abkh3z1osC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In Blaming Islam, John Bowen uncovers the myths about Islam and Muslim integration into Western society, with a focus on the histories, policy, and rhetoric associated with Muslim immigration in Europe, the British experiment with sharia ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Blaming Islam\", \"authors\": [\"John R. Bowen\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=b1Abkh3z1osC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 144, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"MIT Press\", \"categories\": [\"Political Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b1Abkh3z1osC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b1Abkh3z1osC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Why fears about Muslim integration into Western society—propagated opportunistically by some on the right—misread history and misunderstand multiculturalism. In the United States and in Europe, politicians, activists, and even some scholars argue that Islam is incompatible with Western values and that we put ourselves at risk if we believe that Muslim immigrants can integrate into our society. Norway\'s Anders Behring Breivik took this argument to its extreme and murderous conclusion in July 2011. Meanwhile in the United States, state legislatures\' efforts to ban the practice of Islamic law, or sharia, are gathering steam—despite a notable lack of evidence that sharia poses any real threat. In Blaming Islam, John Bowen uncovers the myths about Islam and Muslim integration into Western society, with a focus on the histories, policy, and rhetoric associated with Muslim immigration in Europe, the British experiment with sharia law for Muslim domestic disputes, and the claims of European and American writers that Islam threatens the West. Most important, he shows how exaggerated fears about Muslims misread history, misunderstand multiculturalism\'s aims, and reveal the opportunism of right wing parties who draw populist support by blaming Islam.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=b1Abkh3z1osC&printsec=frontcover&dq=islam&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"2012-03-02\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.3.3.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=b1Abkh3z1osC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780262301107\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0262301105\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"u0sDEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"b8/6kYGLuuI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 103500000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 82800000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-u0sDEAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 103.5, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 82.8, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/u0sDEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Contesting_Islam_Constructing_Race_and_S-sample-pdf.acsm?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Contesting_Islam_Constructing_Race_and_S-sample-epub.acsm?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Hegel&#39;s Interpretation of <b>Islam</b> between Judaism and Christianity&#39;, 208. 124. Anidjar, The Jew, the Arab, 131. 125. Almond, History of <b>Islam</b> in German Thought. 126. Steunebrink, &#39;A Religion after Christianity?\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Contesting Islam, Constructing Race and Sexuality\", \"authors\": [\"Sunera Thobani\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Inordinate Desire of the West\", \"pageCount\": 272, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Bloomsbury Publishing\", \"categories\": [\"Philosophy\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The current political standoffs of the \'War on Terror\' illustrate that the interaction within and between the so-called Western and Middle Eastern civilizations is constantly in flux. A recurring theme however is how Islam and Muslims signify the \'Enemy\' in the Western socio-cultural imagination and have become the \'Other\' against which the West identifies itself. In a unique and insightful blend of critical race, feminist and post-colonial theory, Sunera Thobani examines how Islam is foundational to the formation of Western identity at critical points in its history, including the Crusades, the Reconquista and the colonial period. More specifically, she explores how masculinity and femininity are formed at such pivotal junctures and what role feminism has played in the wars against \'radical\' Islam. Exposing these symbiotic relationships, Thobani explores how the return of \'religion\' is reworking the racial, gender and sexual politics by which Western society defines itself, and more specifically, defines itself against Islam. Contesting Islam, Constructing Race and Sexuality unpacks conventional as well as unconventional orthodoxies to open up new spaces in how we think about sexual and racial identity in the West and the crucial role that Islam has had and continues to have in its development.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT273&dq=islam&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-12-10\", \"contentVersion\": \"2.2.3.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=u0sDEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781350148116\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1350148113\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"oUuWEpkqCNAC\", \"etag\": \"SuyXIffocGk\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/oUuWEpkqCNAC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\