e\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1929280815\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"PXgzDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"ijdCVtrmwQo\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 19990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 9990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-PXgzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 19.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 9.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/PXgzDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Consuming_Japan-sample-pdf.acsm?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Consuming_Japan-sample-epub.acsm?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This insightful book explores the intense and ultimately fleeting moment in 1980s America when the future looked Japanese.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Consuming Japan\", \"authors\": [\"Andrew C. McKevitt\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Popular Culture and the Globalizing of 1980s America\", \"pageCount\": 288, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"UNC Press Books\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This insightful book explores the intense and ultimately fleeting moment in 1980s America when the future looked Japanese. Would Japan\'s remarkable post–World War II economic success enable the East Asian nation to overtake the United States? Or could Japan\'s globe-trotting corporations serve as a model for battered U.S. industries, pointing the way to a future of globalized commerce and culture? While popular films and literature recycled old anti-Asian imagery and crafted new ways of imagining the \\\"yellow peril,\\\" and formal U.S.-Japan relations remained locked in a holding pattern of Cold War complacency, a remarkable shift was happening in countless local places throughout the United States: Japanese goods were remaking American consumer life and injecting contemporary globalization into U.S. commerce and culture. What impact did the flood of billions of Japanese things have on the ways Americans produced, consumed, and thought about their place in the world? From autoworkers to anime fans, Consuming Japan introduces new unorthodox actors into foreign-relations history, demonstrating how the flow of all things Japanese contributed to the globalizing of America in the late twentieth century.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=japan&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2017-08-31\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.0.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PXgzDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781469634487\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1469634481\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"NBUTCgAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"WYABQLsYMbs\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 24950000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 24950000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-NBUTCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 24.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 24.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/NBUTCgAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Lost_Wolves_of_Japan-sample-pdf.acsm?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Lost_Wolves_of_Japan-sample-epub.acsm?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Through poisoning, hired hunters, and a bounty system, one of the archipelago&#39;s largest carnivores was systematically erased. The story of wolf extinction exposes the underside of Japan&#39;s modernization.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Lost Wolves of Japan\", \"authors\": [\"Brett L. Walker\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 360, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Washington Press\", \"categories\": [\"Technology & Engineering\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Many Japanese once revered the wolf as Oguchi no Magami, or Large-Mouthed Pure God, but as Japan began its modern transformation wolves lost their otherworldly status and became noxious animals that needed to be killed. By 1905 they had disappeared from the country. In this spirited and absorbing narrative, Brett Walker takes a deep look at the scientific, cultural, and environmental dimensions of wolf extinction in Japan and tracks changing attitudes toward nature through Japan\'s long history. Grain farmers once worshiped wolves at shrines and left food offerings near their dens, beseeching the elusive canine to protect their crops from the sharp hooves and voracious appetites of wild boars and deer. Talismans and charms adorned with images of wolves protected against fire, disease, and other calamities and brought fertility to agrarian communities and to couples hoping to have children. The Ainu people believed that they were born from the union of a wolflike creature and a goddess. In the eighteenth century, wolves were seen as rabid man-killers in many parts of Japan. Highly ritualized wolf hunts were instigated to cleanse the landscape of what many considered as demons. By the nineteenth century, however, the destruction of wolves had become decidedly unceremonious, as seen on the island of Hokkaido. Through poisoning, hired hunters, and a bounty system, one of the archipelago\'s largest carnivores was systematically erased. The story of wolf extinction exposes the underside of Japan\'s modernization. Certain wolf scientists still camp out in Japan to listen for any trace of the elusive canines. The quiet they experience reminds us of the profound silence that awaits all humanity when, as the Japanese priest Kenko taught almost seven centuries ago, we \\\"look on fellow sentient creatures without feeling compassion.\\\"\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=japan&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2009-11-23\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.18.16.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NBUTCgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780295989938\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0295989939\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"LObyod08_H0C\", \"etag\": \"jtfFxvRreMw\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/LObyod08_H0C\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Japan_That_Never_Was-sample-pdf.acsm?id=LObyod08_H0C&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Japan_That_Never_Was-sample-epub.acsm?id=LObyod08_H0C&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"view