rce=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Contemporary North and South Korea are nations of radical contrasts: one a bellicose totalitarian state with a failing economy; the other a peaceful democracy with a strong economy. Yet their people share a common history that extends back more than 3,000 years. In this comprehensive new history of Korea from the prehistoric era to the present day, Jinwung Kim recounts the rich and fascinating story of the political, social, cultural, economic, and diplomatic developments in Korea\'s long march to the present. He provides a detailed account of the origins of the Korean people and language and the founding of the first walled-town states, along with the advanced civilization that existed in the ancient land of \\\"Unified Silla.\\\" Clarifying the often complex history of the Three Kingdoms Period, Kim chronicles the five-century long history of the Choson dynasty, which left a deep impression on Korean culture. From the beginning, China has loomed large in the history of Korea, from the earliest times when the tribes that would eventually make up the Korean nation roamed the vast plains of Manchuria and against whom Korea would soon define itself. Japan, too, has played an important role in Korean history, particularly in the 20th century; Kim tells this story as well, including the conflicts that led to the current divided state. The first detailed overview of Korean history in nearly a quarter century, this volume will enlighten a new generation of students eager to understand this contested region of Asia.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=s2EVi-MpnUsC&printsec=frontcover&dq=korea&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"2012\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.0.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/A_History_of_Korea.html?hl=&id=s2EVi-MpnUsC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780253000248\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0253000246\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"gM-N2ZXa0YoC\", \"etag\": \"vXtSAwqNYI8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/gM-N2ZXa0YoC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/A_History_of_Korea-sample-pdf.acsm?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/A_History_of_Korea-sample-epub.acsm?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Presenting the richness of Korean civilization from early state formation to the jarring transformations resulting in two distinctive trajectories of modern development, this book introduces the country&#39;s major historical events, patterns, ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"A History of Korea\", \"authors\": [\"Kyung Moon Hwang\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&dq=korea&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 328, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Macmillan International Higher Education\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Presenting the richness of Korean civilization from early state formation to the jarring transformations resulting in two distinctive trajectories of modern development, this book introduces the country\'s major historical events, patterns, and debates. Organised both chronologically and thematically, the 27 concise chapters explore recurring themes such as Korean identity, external influence, and family and gender. This lively narrative assumes no prior knowledge, inviting readers to appreciate both the distinctiveness and universality of Korean history.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC&printsec=frontcover&dq=korea&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2010-10-06\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.8.10.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/A_History_of_Korea.html?hl=&id=gM-N2ZXa0YoC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780230364530\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0230364535\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"2yjwCwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"6UKhefWPiCU\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 19990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 9990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-2yjwCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 19.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 9.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/2yjwCwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Developmental_Mindset-sample-epub.acsm?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The developmental mindset has a long history in Korea but is subject to the vicissitudes of political and economic circumstances.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Developmental Mindset\", \"authors\": [\"Elizabeth Thurbon\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Revival of Financial Activism in South Korea\", \"pageCount\": 240, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Cornell University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Political Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The Asian financial crisis of 1997–1998 was supposed to be the death knell for the developmental state. The International Monetary Fund supplied emergency funds for shattered economies but demanded that states liberalize financial markets and withdraw from direct involvement in the economy. Financial liberalization was meant to spell the end of strategic industry policy and the state-directed \\\"policy lending\\\" it involved. Yet, largely unremarked by analysts, South Korea has since seen a striking revival of financial activism. Policy lending by state-owned development banks has returned the state to the core of the financial system. Korean development banks now account for one quarter of all loans and take the lead in providing low-cost finance to local manufacturing firms in strategic industries. Elizabeth Thurbon argues that an ideational analysis can help explain this renewed financial activism. She demonstrates the presence of a \\\"developmental mindset\\\" on the part of political leaders and policy elites in Korea. This mindset involves shared ways of thinking about the purpose of finance and its relationship to the productive economy. The developmental mindset has a long history in Korea but is subject to the vicissitudes of political and economic circumstances. Thurbon traces the structural, institutional, political, and ideational factors that have strengthened and at times weakened the developmental consensus, culminating in the revival of financial activism in Korea. In doing so, Thurbon offers a novel defense of the developmental state idea and a new framework for investigating the emergence and evolution of developmental states. She also canvasses the implications of the Korean experience for wider debates concerning the future of financial activism in an era of financialization, energy insecurity, and climate change.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=korea&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2016-06-09\", \"contentVersion\": \"2.5.4.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2yjwCwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781501704161\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1501704168\"}], \"panelizatio