gle.com/books/reader?id=5XqpBgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This book recommends bold, policy-oriented prescriptions for overcoming problems in Japan–South Korea relations and facilitating trilateral cooperation among these three Northeast Asian allies, recognizing the power of the public on ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Japan–South Korea Identity Clash\", \"authors\": [\"Brad Glosserman\", \"Scott A. Snyder\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=5XqpBgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"East Asian Security and the United States\", \"pageCount\": 224, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Columbia University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Political Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5XqpBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5XqpBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Japan and South Korea are Western-style democracies with open-market economies committed to the rule of law. They are also U.S. allies. Yet despite their shared interests, shared values, and geographic proximity, divergent national identities have driven a wedge between them. Drawing on decades of expertise, Brad Glosserman and Scott A. Snyder investigate the roots of this split and its ongoing threat to the region and the world. Glosserman and Snyder isolate competing notions of national identity as the main obstacle to a productive partnership between Japan and South Korea. Through public opinion data, interviews, and years of observation, they show how fundamentally incompatible, rapidly changing conceptions of national identity in Japan and South Korea—and not struggles over power or structural issues—have complicated territorial claims and international policy. Despite changes in the governments of both countries and concerted efforts by leading political figures to encourage U.S.–ROK–Japan security cooperation, the Japan–South Korea relationship continues to be hobbled by history and its deep imprint on ideas of national identity. This book recommends bold, policy-oriented prescriptions for overcoming problems in Japan–South Korea relations and facilitating trilateral cooperation among these three Northeast Asian allies, recognizing the power of the public on issues of foreign policy, international relations, and the prospects for peace in Asia.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=5XqpBgAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=korea&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2015-05-26\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.4.4.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=5XqpBgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780231539289\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0231539282\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 2500}'),('mars','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"4W-2DwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"dGZwbiO4EaQ\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 14990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 14990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-4W-2DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 14.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 14.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/4W-2DwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Big_Book_of_Mars-sample-pdf.acsm?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Big_Book_of_Mars-sample-epub.acsm?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The most comprehensive look at our relationship with Mars—yesterday, today, and tomorrow—through history, archival images, pop culture ephemera, and interviews with NASA scientists Mars has been a source of fascination and speculation ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Big Book of Mars\", \"authors\": [\"Marc Hartzman\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"From Ancient Egypt to The Martian, A Deep-Space Dive into Our Obsession with the Red Planet\", \"pageCount\": 236, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Quirk Books\", \"categories\": [\"Social Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Filled with entertaining history, archival images, pop culture ephemera, and interviews with NASA scientists, The Big Book of Mars is the most comprehensive look at our relationship with Mars—yesterday, today, and tomorrow. Mars has been a source of fascination and speculation ever since the Ancient Sumerians observed its blood-red hue and named it for their god of war and plague. But it wasn\'t until 1877, when \\\"canals\\\" were observed on the surface of the Red Planet, suggesting the presence of water, that scientists, novelists, filmmakers, and entrepreneurs became obsessed with the question of whether there\'s life on Mars. In The War of the Worlds, H.G. Wells suggested that we wouldn\'t need to make contact with Martians—they\'d come for us—while, many years later, Nikola Tesla claimed that he did make contact. Since then, Mars has fully invaded pop culture. It has its own day of the week (Tuesday, or martis in Latin), candy bar, and iconic Looney Tunes character. It has been the subject of novels and movies, from Ray Bradbury\'s The Martian Chronicles to Mars Attacks! to The Martian. And it has sparked a space-race feud between Elon Musk and Jeff Bezos, who both hope to send a manned mission to Mars in the near future.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=mars&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-07-07\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.3.2.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4W-2DwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781683692102\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1683692101\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"diixDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"dXBuEcfZkRM\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 11990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 11990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-diixDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 11.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 11.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/diixDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Sirens_of_Mars-sample-epub.acsm?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In this beautifully observed, deeply personal book, Georgetown scientist Sarah Stewart Johnson tells the story of how she and other researchers have scoured Mars for signs of life, transforming the planet from a distant point of light into ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Sirens of Mars\", \"authors\": [\"Sarah Stewart Johnson\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Searching for Life on Another World\", \"pageCount\": 304, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Crown\", \"categories\": [\"Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"“Sarah Stewart Johnson interweaves her own coming-of-age story as a planetary scientist with a vivid history of the exploration of Mars in this celebration of human curiosity, passion, and perseverance.”—Alan Lightman, author of Einstein’s Dreams WINNER OF THE PHI BETA KAPPA AWARD FOR SCIENCE • NAMED ONE OF THE BEST BOOKS OF THE YEAR BY The New York Times Book Review • Times (UK) • Library Journal “Lovely . . . Johnson’s prose swirls with lyrical wonder, as varied and multihued as the apricot deserts, butterscotch skies and blue sunsets of Mars.”—Anthony Doerr, The New York Times Book Review Mars was once similar to Earth, but today there are no rivers, no lakes, no oceans. Coated in red dust, the terrain is bewilderingly empty. And yet multiple spacecraft are circling Mars, sweeping over Terra Sabaea, Syrtis Major, the dunes of Elysium, and Mare Sirenum—on the brink, perhaps, of a staggering find, one that would inspire humankind as much as any discovery in the history of modern science. In this beautifully observed, deeply personal book, Georgetown scientist Sarah Stewart Johnson tells the story of how she and other researchers have scoured Mars for signs of life, transforming the planet from a distant point of light into a world of its own. Johnson’s fascination with Mars began as a child in Kentucky, turning over rocks with her father and looking at planets in the night sky. She now conducts fieldwork in some of Earth’s most hostile environments, such as the Dry Valleys of Antarctica and the salt flats of Western Australia, developing methods for detecting life on other worlds. Here, with poetic precision, she interlaces her own personal journey—as a female scientist and a mother—with tales of other seekers, from Percival Lowell, who was convinced that a utopian society existed on Mars, to Audouin Dollfus, who tried to carry out astronomical observations from a stratospheric balloon. In the process, she shows how the story of Mars is also a story about Earth: This other world has been our mirror, our foil, a telltale reflection of our own anxieties and yearnings. Empathetic and evocative, The Sirens of Mars offers an unlikely natural history of a place where no human has ever set foot, while providing a vivid portrait of our quest to defy our isolation in the cosmos.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=diixDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=mars&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 5, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-07-07\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.5.5.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=diixDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781101904824\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1101904828\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"Dy0kDQAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"Djl7F9T9AD8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/Dy0kDQAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=Dy0kDQAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Filled with vivid photographs taken on Earth, in space, and on Mars; arresting maps; and commentary from the world&#39;s top planetary scientists, this fascinating book will take you millions of miles away--and decades into