tent?id=J8CGDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The first published book by the creator of Tarzan of the Apes that introduced the world to intergalactic Civil War soldier, John Carter Two years before Edgar Rice Burroughs became a worldwide celebrity with the publication of Tarzan of the Apes and its twenty-two sequels, which together have sold more than 30 million copies, he published the futuristic sci-fi romance, A Princess of Mars. A Princess of Mars tells the story of John Carter, a Civil War veteran who inexplicably finds himself held prisoner on the planet Mars by the Green Men of Thark. With Dejah Thoris, the princess of another clan on Mars, John Carter must fight for their freedom and save the entire planet from destruction as the life-sustaining Atmosphere Factory slowly grinds to a halt. A Princess of Mars is the first in Burroughs\' eleven book Barsoon series, following the continued adventures of John Carter. For more than seventy years, Penguin has been the leading publisher of classic literature in the English-speaking world. With more than 1,700 titles, Penguin Classics represents a global bookshelf of the best works throughout history and across genres and disciplines. Readers trust the series to provide authoritative texts enhanced by introductions and notes by distinguished scholars and contemporary authors, as well as up-to-date translations by award-winning translators.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=J8CGDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=mars&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 95, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2007-01-30\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/A_Princess_of_Mars.html?hl=&id=J8CGDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780143104889\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0143104888\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"S2pzBgAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"BYTDPYc2JpY\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 3990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 3990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-S2pzBgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 3.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 3.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/S2pzBgAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Discovering_Mars_The_Amazing_Story_of_th-sample-pdf.acsm?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Discovering_Mars_The_Amazing_Story_of_th-sample-epub.acsm?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Featuring incredible photos and new information about the latest research into Mars, this updated edition of DISCOVERING MARS covers everything about the great red planet, from past to present.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Discovering Mars: The Amazing Story of the Red Planet\", \"authors\": [\"Melvin Berger\", \"Mary Kay Carson\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 64, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Scholastic Inc.\", \"categories\": [\"Juvenile Nonfiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Featuring incredible photos and new information about the latest research into Mars, this updated edition of DISCOVERING MARS covers everything about the great red planet, from past to present. Topics include myths and facts about life on Mars, a history of NASA\'s Mars research, including the Rover missions, and ideas about our potential future relationship with the planet. With its lively text narrative and beautiful color photos, students and teachers alike will enjoy learning everything there is to know about Mars.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=mars&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2015-08-25\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.6.7.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=S2pzBgAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780545860154\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0545860156\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"ze27j5sSJVEC\", \"etag\": \"thRjofXB/V8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/ze27j5sSJVEC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=ze27j5sSJVEC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This volume fills that gap by providing a summary of what is presently known about Mars and identifying many puzzles such as polar cap variance, occurrence of dust storms, and the possible location of water.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Mars\", \"authors\": [\"Hugh H. Kieffer\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=ze27j5sSJVEC&dq=mars&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Maps\", \"pageCount\": 1498, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Arizona Press\", \"categories\": [\"Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ze27j5sSJVEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ze27j5sSJVEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"The planet Mars has been a subject of wonder for millennia, as attested by its place in mythology, by later speculation about its canals, and by the scientific and public excitement over the Viking mission. Although the scientific literature about the planet is voluminous, no comprehensive treatment of the results of modern spacecraft exploration has yet been made available. This volume fills that gap by providing a summary of what is presently known about Mars and identifying many puzzles such as polar cap variance, occurrence of dust storms, and the possible location of water. The introductory chapter cites questions, controversies, and milestones in the study of Mars, and also includes an annotated book list, basic data about the planet, and a guide to Martian seasons. A chapter on telescopic observation credits the contributions made by many amateurs that have advanced our knowledge of variations observed on Mars. A chapter on spacecraft exploration, by an American and a Russian author who have participated in all Mars missions, includes a revelation of an additional Soviet attempt. Twenty-nine technical articles cover geophysics; bedrock geology; surface; atmosphere; exosphere and magnetic field; and climate history. Two chapters address the search for life on Mars; three concluding chapters consider the Martian satellites. An indispensable reference for scientists, Mars will also serve as a complete sourcebook for serious amateur astronomers.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=ze27j5sSJVEC&printsec=frontcover&dq=mars&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"1992-10\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.0.1.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Mars.html?hl=&id=ze27j5sSJVEC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0816512574\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780816512577\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"m_EfAQAAIAAJ\", \"etag\": \"555gjEjjq1E\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/m_EfAQAAIAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=m_EfAQAAIAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Illustrated throughout, this work contains surface and orbital images from Spirit, Opportunity, Mars Express, the Hubble Space Telescope and Earth-based observations - plus historic images depicting Mars in fiction and mythology, movie ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Real Mars\", \"authors\": [\"Michael Hanlon\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=m_EfAQAAIAAJ&dq=mars&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 250, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"categories\": [\"Mars (Planet)\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m_EfAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m_EfAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Illustrated throughout, this work contains surface and orbital images from Spirit, Opportunity, Mars Express, the Hubble Space Telescope and Earth-based observations - plus historic images depicting Mars in fiction and mythology, movie images, and drawings that adorned the pulp sci-fi stories of the 1930s.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=m_EfAQAAIAAJ&q=mars&dq=mars&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2004\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.3.3.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Real_Mars.html?hl=&id=m_EfAQAAIAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"OTHER\", \"identifier\": \"STANFORD:36105119478480\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"zJ9EEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"kcAdP5yHgc0\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 30000000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 16500000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 30, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 16.5, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/zJ9EEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Discovering_Mars-sample-pdf.acsm?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Discovering_Mars-sample-epub.acsm?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The story is epic in scope—an Iliad or Odyssey for our time, at least so far largely without the folly, greed, lust, and tragedy of those ancient stories.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Discovering Mars\", \"authors\": [\"William Sheehan\", \"Jim Bell\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A History of Observation and Exploration of the Red Planet\", \"pageCount\": 712, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Arizona Press\", \"categories\": [\"Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"For millenia humans have considered Mars the most fascinating planet in our solar system. We’ve watched this Earth-like world first with the naked eye, then using telescopes, and, most recently, through robotic orbiters and landers and rovers on the surface. Historian William Sheehan and astronomer and planetary scientist Jim Bell combine their talents to tell a unique story of what we’ve learned by studying Mars through evolving technologies. What the eye sees as a mysterious red dot wandering through the sky becomes a blurry mirage of apparent seas, continents, and canals as viewed through Earth-based telescopes. Beginning with the Mariner and Viking missions of the 1960s and 1970s, space-based instruments and monitoring systems have flooded scientists with data on Mars’s meteorology and geology, and have even sought evidence of possible existence of life-forms on or beneath the surface. This knowledge has transformed our perception of the Red Planet and has provided clues for better understanding our own blue world. Discovering Mars vividly conveys the way our understanding of this other planet has grown from earliest times to the present. The story is epic in scope—an Iliad or Odyssey for our time, at least so far largely without the folly, greed, lust, and tragedy of those ancient stories. Instead, the narrative of our quest for the Red Planet has showcased some of our species’ most hopeful attributes: curiosity, cooperation, exploration, and the restless drive to understand our place in the larger universe. Sheehan and Bell have written an ambitious first draft of that narrative even as the latest chapters continue to be added both by researchers on Earth and our robotic emissaries on and around Mars, including the latest: the Perseverance rover and its Ingenuity helicopter drone, which set down in Mars’s Jezero Crater in February 2021.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=mars&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-10-19\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=zJ9EEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780816544240\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0816544247\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"Ld9jAwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"ttiyav0lXGw\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 7990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 7990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 7.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 7.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/Ld9jAwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/How_We_ll_Live_on_Mars-sample-epub.acsm?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In this sweeping, provocative book that mixes business, science, and human reporting, Petranek makes the case that living on Mars is an essential back-up plan for humanity and explains in fascinating detail just how it will happen.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"How We\'ll Live on Mars\", \"authors\": [\"Stephen Petranek\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 96, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Simon and Schuster\", \"categories\": [\"Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Award-winning journalist Stephen Petranek says humans will live on Mars by 2027. Now he makes the case that living on Mars is not just plausible, but inevitable. It sounds like science fiction, but Stephen Petranek considers it fact: Within twenty years, humans will live on Mars. We’ll need to. In this sweeping, provocative book that mixes business, science, and human reporting, Petranek makes the case that living on Mars is an essential back-up plan for humanity and explains in fascinating detail just how it will happen. The race is on. Private companies, driven by iconoclastic entrepreneurs, such as Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, Paul Allen, and Sir Richard Branson; Dutch reality show and space mission Mars One; NASA; and the Chinese government are among the many groups competing to plant the first stake on Mars and open the door for human habitation. Why go to Mars? Life on Mars has potential life-saving possibilities for everyone on earth. Depleting water supplies, overwhelming climate change, and a host of other disasters—from terrorist attacks to meteor strikes—all loom large. We must become a space-faring species to survive. We have the technology not only to get humans to Mars, but to convert Mars into another habitable planet. It will likely take 300 years to “terraform” Mars, as the jargon goes, but we can turn it into a veritable second Garden of Eden. And we can live there, in specially designed habitations, within the next twenty years. In this exciting chronicle, Petranek introduces the circus of lively characters all engaged in a dramatic effort to be the first to settle the Red Planet. How We’ll Live on Mars brings firsthand reporting, interviews with key participants, and extensive research to bear on the question of how we can expect to see life on Mars within the next twenty years.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=mars&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 4, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2015-07-07\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.13.11.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Ld9jAwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781476784779\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1476784779\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"3ND8zQEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"ZkUptdbmAgE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/3ND8zQEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=3ND8zQEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This book is dedicated to the nascent discussion of the legal aspects of human exploration and possible settlement of Mars, and provides fresh insights and new ideas in two key areas.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Assessing a Mars Agreement Including Human Settlements\", \"authors\": [\"Annette Froehlich\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=3ND8zQEACAAJ&dq=mars&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 205, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Springer\", \"categories\": [\"Law\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3ND8zQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3ND8zQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This book is dedicated to the nascent discussion of the legal aspects of human exploration and possible settlement of Mars, and provides fresh insights and new ideas in two key areas. The first one revolves around the broader aspects of current space law, such as intellectual property rights in outer space, the legal implications of contact with extra-terrestrial intelligence, legal considerations around the freedom of exploration and use, and the International Space Station agreement as a precedent for Mars. The second one focuses on the creation and management of a new society on Mars, and includes topics such as human reproduction and childbirth, the protection of human rights in privately-funded settlements, legal aspects of a Martian power grid, and criminal justice on the red planet. With multiple national space agencies and commercial enterprises focusing on Mars, it is more than likely that a human presence will be established on the red planet in the coming decades. While the foundation of international space law, laid primarily by the Outer Space Treaty, remains the framework within which humans will engage with Mars, new and unforeseen challenges have arisen, driven particularly by the rapid pace of technological advancement in recent years. To ensure that space law can keep up with these developments, a new scholarly work such as the present one is critical. By bringing together a number of fresh international perspectives on the topic, the book is of interest to all scholars and professionals working in the space field.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=3ND8zQEACAAJ&dq=mars&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-05-03\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Assessing_a_Mars_Agreement_Including_Hum.html?hl=&id=3ND8zQEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"303065012X\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9783030650124\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 2323}'),('michael','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"jJjPjwEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"Ij3kd3sPPac\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/jJjPjwEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=jJjPjwEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Joseph Goebbels, born in 1897, aspired to be an author, obtained a Ph.D from the University of Heidelberg in 1921.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Michael\", \"authors\": [\"Josef Goebbels\", \"Adolf Hitler\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=jJjPjwEACAAJ&dq=michael&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Novel\", \"pageCount\": 158, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Grand Oak Books\", \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jJjPjwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jJjPjwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Joseph Goebbels, born in 1897, aspired to be an author, obtained a Ph.D from the University of Heidelberg in 1921. He joined the Nazi Party in 1924, After the Nazi seizure of power in 1933, Goebbels\' Propaganda Ministry quickly gained and exerted controlling supervision over the news media, arts, and information in Germany. In 1943, Goebbels began to pressure Hitler to introduce measures that would produce \\\"total war,\\\" including closing businesses not essential to the war effort, conscripting women into the labor force, and enlisting men in previously exempt occupations into the Wehrmacht. Hitler finally appointed him as Reich Plenipotentiary for Total War on 23 July 1944, whereby Goebbels undertook largely unsuccessful measures to increase the number of people available for armaments production and the Wehrmacht. As the war drew to a close and Nazi Germany faced defeat, his wife Magda and their children joined him in Berlin. They moved into Hitler\'s bunker. Hitler committed suicide on April 20, 1945. In accordance with Hitler\'s will, Goebbels succeeded him as Reichschancellor; he served one day in this post. The following day, Goebbels and his wife committed suicide, after poisoning their six children with cyanide. Stephen R. Pastore is a novelist, playwright, poet and literary biographer/bibliographer. Born in New York City, he is the author of The Art of Adolf Hitler, The Complete Paintings of Adolf Hitler, Adolf Before He Was Hitler and is the editor of Mein Kampf: A Descriptive Bibliography.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=jJjPjwEACAAJ&dq=michael&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2016-05-11\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Michael.html?hl=&id=jJjPjwEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1937727653\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781937727659\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"Eb3lwAEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"adU/wWMlkxE\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/Eb3lwAEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=Eb3lwAEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Readers are treated to a detailed introduction to Michael and his many appearances. The rest of this practical guide provides a variety of methods for connecting with Michael, petitioning his help, and creating a lasting bond.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Michael\", \"authors\": [\"Richard Webster\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Eb3lwAEACAAJ&dq=michael&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Communicating with the Archangel for Guidance & Protection\", \"pageCount\": 167, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Llewellyn Worldwide Limited\", \"categories\": [\"Body, Mind & Spirit\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Eb3lwAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Eb3lwAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Michael is considered the greatest angel in the Christian, Judaic, and Islamic traditions. Throughout the ages, he has appeared as a protector, a messenger, a guide, a warrior, and a healer. In Michael, Richard Webster presents a thorough history of this famous archangel and offers simple techniques for contacting him. Readers are treated to a detailed introduction to Michael and his many appearances. The rest of this practical guide provides a variety of methods for connecting with Michael, petitioning his help, and creating a lasting bond. Through easy-to-perform rituals and meditations-some involving candle magic, crystals, and dreamwork-readers will learn how to get in touch with the Prince of Light for courage, protection, strength, and spiritual guidance.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Eb3lwAEACAAJ&dq=michael&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2004\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Michael.html?hl=&id=Eb3lwAEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0738705403\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780738705408\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"6gFaPwAACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"yiNM1YCMa0s\"