ntifier\": \"9781442055506\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"vBYAuAAACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"r0nJm7ZKFec\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/vBYAuAAACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=vBYAuAAACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In War Room, New York Times bestselling author Michael Holley gives readers an unprecedented look behind the scenes at three contending National Football League teams—from the draft room to the locker room to the sidelines—and grants ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"War Room\", \"authors\": [\"Michael Holley\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=vBYAuAAACAAJ&dq=michael&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Legacy of Bill Belichick and the Art of Building the Perfect Team\", \"pageCount\": 352, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"It Books\", \"categories\": [\"Sports & Recreation\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vBYAuAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vBYAuAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"In War Room, New York Times bestselling author Michael Holley gives readers an unprecedented look behind the scenes at three contending National Football League teams—from the draft room to the locker room to the sidelines—and grants access to the brilliant minds of Bill Belichick and his former protÉgÉs, Thomas Dimitroff and Scott Pioli. In 1991, while he was with the Cleveland Browns football organization, Belichick was struck by the Big Idea: how to build the perfect team, one draft pick and one trade at a time. This strategy obsessed him, leading him on a remarkable personal and professional journey filled with miraculous finishes, heartbreaking losses, shattered relationships . . . and ultimately three Super Bowl championships. In Massachusetts, Belichick reunited with two former office employees from the Ohio days—Pioli, a low-paid scouting assistant, and Dimitroff, a groundskeeper and part-time scout—and together they refined and burnished Belichick\'s method for constructing a winning team. The end result was one of the greatest franchises in modern NFL history: the New England Patriots. Packed with never-before-told anecdotes and insights from team officials, players, coaches, and scouts, War Room is a fascinating, often astonishing story of grit and genius, and the art of building a championship team.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=vBYAuAAACAAJ&dq=michael&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2012-09-04\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/War_Room.html?hl=&id=vBYAuAAACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"006208240X\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780062082404\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"pudKEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"Q+xnPq1TfZ4\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/pudKEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=pudKEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Here is the inspiring story behind the Veterans Day red poppy, a symbol that honors the service and sacrifices of our veterans.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Poppy Lady\", \"authors\": [\"Barbara E. Walsh\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=pudKEAAAQBAJ&dq=michael&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Moina Belle Michael and Her Tribute to Veterans\", \"pageCount\": 40, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Archie Comic Publications (Trade)\", \"categories\": [\"Juvenile Nonfiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pudKEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pudKEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Here is the inspiring story behind the Veterans Day red poppy, a symbol that honors the service and sacrifices of our veterans. When American soldiers entered World War I, Moina Belle Michael, a schoolteacher from Georgia, knew she had to act. Some of the soldiers were her students and friends. Almost single-handedly, Moina worked to establish the red poppy as the symbol to honor and remember soldiers. And she devoted the rest of her life to making sure the symbol would last forever. Thanks to her hard work, that symbol remains strong today. Author Barbara Elizabeth Walsh and artist Layne Johnson worked with experts, primary documents, and Moina\'s great-nieces to better understand Moina\'s determination to honor the war veterans. A portion of the book\'s proceeds will support the National Military Family Association\'s Operation Purple®, which benefits children of the U.S. military.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=pudKEAAAQBAJ&dq=michael&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 1, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3, \"publishedDate\": \"2012-09-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Poppy_Lady.html?hl=&id=pudKEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781590787540\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1590787544\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"dLy6BwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"9YitbuBGAR8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/dLy6BwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dLy6BwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In this Very Short Introduction, Michael Freeden explores the concept of liberalism, one of the longest-standing and central political theories and ideologies.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Liberalism\", \"authors\": [\"Michael Freeden\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=dLy6BwAAQBAJ&dq=michael&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Very Short Introduction\", \"pageCount\": 143, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Oxford University Press, USA\", \"categories\": [\"Philosophy\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dLy6BwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=c