ink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=F4G1oAEACAAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Untold Story of Mike Tyson\", \"pageCount\": 354, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Day Owl PressCorp\", \"categories\": [\"Biography & Autobiography\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F4G1oAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F4G1oAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Mike Tyson was the beast. Rory Holloway was his handler. Their lives in the spotlight were a zoo. In the 1990s, one man ruled the world of heavyweight boxing, Mike Tyson. He drove his fist through opponents\' skulls, raked in multi-millions of dollars and bedded other men\'s wives and their daughters. That much is a matter of record. You think yoiu know the story? You\'ve barely scratched the surface. The Handler: Rory Holloway: Rory was Mike\'s closest friend. He gathered a tight-knit team and soon had Mike on track to be the world\'s first billion-dollar athlete. When Mike bared his teeth in the rematch with Evander Holyfield, the world was stunned. Mike hid away, fired his team and lost his hold on greatness, while Rory did the hardest thing of all. He kept quiet. He guarded secrets...Until now.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=F4G1oAEACAAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2016-03-25\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Taming_the_Beast.html?hl=&id=F4G1oAEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1940401836\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781940401836\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"mVeDBAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"DEmdwUCxut8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/mVeDBAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=mVeDBAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Covering Mike Tyson&#39;s rise through the amateur and professional boxing ranks, this book follows the Brooklyn native from his early years as a young criminal in Brownsville to his 1988 heavyweight unification match with Michael Spinks.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Rise of Mike Tyson, Heavyweight\", \"authors\": [\"William F. McNeil\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=mVeDBAAAQBAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 252, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"McFarland\", \"categories\": [\"Sports & Recreation\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mVeDBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mVeDBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Covering Mike Tyson\'s rise through the amateur and professional boxing ranks, this book follows the Brooklyn native from his early years as a young criminal in Brownsville to his 1988 heavyweight unification match with Michael Spinks. The book focuses on the Catskill Boxing Club--where boxing guru Cus D\'Amato trained the 210-pound teenager in the finer points of the sport and developed his impregnable defense--and on his home life with D\'Amato and surrogate mother Camille Ewald and the other young fighters who lived with them. Tyson\'s boxing education began in the unauthorized \\\"smokers\\\" held every week in the Bronx, matching his skills against older, more experienced fighters. He won the 1981 Amateur Heavyweight Boxing Championship in Colorado Springs at the age of 14 and repeated the amazing feat the following year. By 1985, finding no other challenging amateur competition, he was forced to join the professional ranks where, in November 1986, he became the youngest heavyweight champion in boxing history. Less than two years later, he unified the crown, establishing himself as one of the most dominant heavyweight fighters the sport had ever seen.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=mVeDBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2014-09-15\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Rise_of_Mike_Tyson_Heavyweight.html?hl=&id=mVeDBAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780786496488\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0786496487\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"fnXurQEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"8RBPZhJFIH8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/fnXurQEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=fnXurQEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This is a side of the Mike Tyson story rarely seen or shared.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Mike Tyson\", \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=fnXurQEACAAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"1981-1991\", \"pageCount\": 100, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Power House Books\", \"categories\": [\"Photography\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fnXurQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fnXurQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"It all began with an art school photography assignment: Lori Grinker was shooting a project on young boxers under the guidance of the legendary trainer Cus D\'Amato. Her main focus became a nine-year-old boxer Billy Hamm. While photographing him, Cus wandered over and asked why Lori was shooting that kid, when the bigger kid in the corner working a speed bag would one day be the heavyweight champion of the world! The kid was a then 13-year-old Mike Tyson. Lori\'s early boxing photographs of Mike Tyson are without peer--little exists from that era and all of Grinker\'s work is personal with uniquely privileged access in and out of the ring. Over the next decade Lori would photograph the coterie that surrounded Mike; Cus\'s funeral, going home to Brownsville, old friends, trips abroad, in hotel suites before and after fights, his hook-up with Robin Givens, their wedding, their divorce, and the training and fights in between until Tyson\'s first defeat--the Buster Douglas fight in 1991. This is a side of the Mike Tyson story rarely seen or shared.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=fnXurQEACAAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2015-10-20\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Mike_Tyson.html?hl=&id=fnXurQEACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1576877760\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781576877760\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"iLnxAQAACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"juqVcRLMIUw\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/iLnxAQAACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=iLnxAQAACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Here is Tyson&#39;s fight-by-fight path to that goal, the millions of dollars made and fought over, the sex and violence of his personal life, and his eventual defeats both in the ring and in court.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Bad Intentions\", \"authors\": [\"Peter Heller\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=iLnxAQAACAAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The Mike Tyson Story\", \"pageCount\": 476, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Da Capo Press\", \"categories\": [\"Sports & Recreation\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iLnxAQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iLnxAQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Mike Tyson is boxing\'s most beloved bad boy. With a history of street-gang violence, juvenile prison, sexual scandal, marital strife, courtroom battles, and imprisonment for rape, he has become one of the most publicized athletes in history. At age 23 he was already considered among the greatest prizefighters of all time, and, his career is far from over. Relying on in-depth research and interviews with those who have known Tyson at every stage of his life, Bad Intentions portrays the shy child who became a vicious street thug, discovered boxing in juvenile prison, and was brought to the attention of the legendary Cus D\'Amato to be shaped to be one thing only—heavyweight champion of the world. Here is Tyson\'s fight-by-fight path to that goal, the millions of dollars made and fought over, the sex and violence of his personal life, and his eventual defeats both in the ring and in court. Bad Intentions is an essential read for all who would understand the ins and outs of the most controversial sport in America.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=iLnxAQAACAAJ&dq=mike+tyson&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"1995-08-22\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Bad_Intentions.html?hl=&id=iLnxAQAACAAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"030680669X\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780306806698\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"9FSvNAEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"76klY4kc/ik\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/9FSvNAEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"