ubtitle\": \"Going Bananas with Pairs\", \"pageCount\": 32, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Bloomsbury Publishing USA\", \"categories\": [\"Juvenile Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LTGapuBtsfIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LTGapuBtsfIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Presents pairs of related items, such as an apple and an orange or a bicycle and a motorcycle, and asks why they are similar, while offering unexpected answers.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=LTGapuBtsfIC&printsec=frontcover&dq=oranges&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2007-12-26\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.121.1.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Apples_and_Oranges.html?hl=&id=LTGapuBtsfIC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781599901039\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"159990103X\"}]}}, {\"id\": \"5A1uDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"wgEGioVW7ZU\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/5A1uDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=5A1uDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Examining the practice of comparison across the study of history, language, religion, and culture, distinguished scholar of religion Bruce Lincoln argues in Apples and Oranges for a comparatism of a more modest sort.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Apples and Oranges\", \"authors\": [\"Bruce Lincoln\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=5A1uDwAAQBAJ&dq=oranges&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Explorations In, On, and With Comparison\", \"pageCount\": 347, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"University of Chicago Press\", \"categories\": [\"Religion\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5A1uDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5A1uDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Comparison is an indispensable intellectual operation that plays a crucial role in the formation of knowledge. Yet comparison often leads us to forego attention to nuance, detail, and context, perhaps leaving us bereft of an ethical obligation to take things correspondingly as they are. Examining the practice of comparison across the study of history, language, religion, and culture, distinguished scholar of religion Bruce Lincoln argues in Apples and Oranges for a comparatism of a more modest sort. Lincoln presents critiques of recent attempts at grand comparison, and enlists numerous theoretical examples of how a more modest, cautious, and discriminating form of comparison might work and what it can accomplish. He does this through studies of shamans, werewolves, human sacrifices, apocalyptic prophecies, sacred kings, and surveys of materials as diverse and wide-ranging as Beowulf, Herodotus’s account of the Scythians, the Native American Ghost Dance, and the Spanish Civil War. Ultimately, Lincoln argues that concentrating one\'s focus on a relatively small number of items that the researcher can compare closely, offering equal attention to relations of similarity and difference, not only grants dignity to all parties considered, it yields more reliable and more interesting—if less grandiose—results. Giving equal attention to the social, historical, and political contexts and subtexts of religious and literary texts also allows scholars not just to assess their content, but also to understand the forces, problems, and circumstances that motivated and shaped them.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=5A1uDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=oranges&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2018-08-23\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Apples_and_Oranges.html?hl=&id=5A1uDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780226564074\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"022656407X\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 2898}'),('planes','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"EdqqBwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"HukxE3kYRP8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/EdqqBwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Art_of_Planes-sample-pdf.acsm?id=EdqqBwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Art_of_Planes-sample-epub.acsm?id=EdqqBwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=EdqqBwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"The Art of Planes explores the beautiful concept art that went into the development of these two inspiring stories, including colorscripts, storyboards, character studies, sculpts, background art, and more.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Art of Planes\", \"authors\": [\"Tracey Miller-Zarneke\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=EdqqBwAAQBAJ&dq=planes&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 176, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Chronicle Books\", \"categories\": [\"Performing Arts\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EdqqBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EdqqBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"In Disney\'s Planes and Planes: Fire and Rescue, the big-hearted crop duster Dusty Crophopper is full of dreams. In the first film, he overcomes his fear of heights to win the Wings Around The Globe Rally. In the second, Dusty learns his damaged engine will keep him from racing, but he finds the true hero within himself working alongside firefighting aircraft on a courageous wildfire air attack team. The Art of Planes explores the beautiful concept art that went into the development of these two inspiring stories, including colorscripts, storyboards, character studies, sculpts, background art, and more. Insider insights from the films\' artists and filmmakers, a preface by directors Bobs Gannaway and Klay Hall, and a foreword by Chief Creative Officer John Lasseter offer an invaluable and fascinating glimpse into the creative thinking involved in the making of these companion films. Copyright ©2014 Disney Enter