books.google.com/books/content?id=MbEWEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"La secuela de Ready Player One, el best seller mundial que Steven Spielberg adaptó al cine. «Esta historia trata sobre ti y sobre la influencia que han tenido los videojuegos en tu vida.» Trevor Noah Días después de ganar la competición ideada por James Halliday, el fundador de OASIS, Wade Watts hace un descubrimiento que lo cambia todo. Oculto en las cajas fuertes de Halliday y a la espera de que lo encuentre su heredero, se halla un avance tecnológico que volverá a cambiar el mundo y convertirá a OASIS en un lugar mil veces más asombroso (y adictivo) de lo que Wade jamás habría creído posible. Dicho avance da pie a un nuevo acertijo y a una nueva misión, un último Huevo de Pascua de Halliday que da a entender que existe un misterioso premio. Wade también se encontrará con un nuevo rival muy peligroso, increíblemente poderoso y capaz de matara millones de personas para conseguir lo que quiere. La vida de Wade y el futuro de OASIS vuelven a estar en juego, pero en esta ocasión también pende de un hilo el destino de la humanidad. Con una nostalgia y una originalidad que solo podrían salir de la mente de Ernest Cline, Ready Player Two nos adentra de nuevo en su querido universo virtual, embarcándonos en otra aventura imaginativa, divertida y llena de acción, y vuelve a impresionarnos con su apasionante representación del futuro. Sobre Ready Player One: «Un libro impresionante. Me pareció que estaba escrito para mí.» Patrick Rothfuss\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=MbEWEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=ready+player&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-03-25\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.2.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=MbEWEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9788418037092\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"8418037091\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"yil0DwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"1Cx6ge2p8XU\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 21990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13190000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-yil0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 21.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.19, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/yil0DwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Ready_Player_Two-sample-pdf.acsm?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Ready_Player_Two-sample-epub.acsm?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Ultimately, this book offers vital prescriptions for how one of our most powerful entertainment industries must evolve its ideas of women.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Ready Player Two\", \"authors\": [\"Shira Chess\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Women Gamers and Designed Identity\", \"pageCount\": 240, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"U of Minnesota Press\", \"categories\": [\"Games & Activities\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Cultural stereotypes to the contrary, approximately half of all video game players are now women. A subculture once dominated by men, video games have become a form of entertainment composed of gender binaries. Supported by games such as Diner Dash, Mystery Case Files, Wii Fit, and Kim Kardashian: Hollywood—which are all specifically marketed toward women—the gamer industry is now a major part of imagining what femininity should look like. In Ready Player Two, media critic Shira Chess uses the concept of “Player Two”—the industry idealization of the female gamer—to examine the assumptions implicit in video games designed for women and how they have impacted gaming culture and the larger society. With Player Two, the video game industry has designed specifically for the feminine ideal: she is white, middle class, heterosexual, cis-gendered, and abled. Drawing on categories from time management and caregiving to social networking, consumption, and bodies, Chess examines how games have been engineered to shape normative ideas about women and leisure. Ready Player Two presents important arguments about how gamers and game developers must change their thinking about both women and games to produce better games, better audiences, and better industry practices. Ultimately, this book offers vital prescriptions for how one of our most powerful entertainment industries must evolve its ideas of women.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=ready+player&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2017-10-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.4.3.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=yil0DwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781452954998\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1452954992\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"edNBPdEwbJUC\", \"etag\": \"AKbrYVc9fE8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/edNBPdEwbJUC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Robopocalypse-sample-epub.acsm?id=edNBPdEwbJUC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=edNBPdEwbJUC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Roughly twenty years from now, our technological marvels unite and turn against us.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Robopocalypse\", \"authors\": [\"Daniel H. Wilson\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=edNBPdEwbJUC&dq=ready+player&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 368, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Simon and Schuster\", \"categories\": [\"Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=edNBPdEwbJUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=edNBPdEwbJUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Roughly twenty years from now, our technological marvels unite and turn against us. A childlike but massively powerful artificial intelligence known as Archos comes online…and kills the man who created it. This first act of betrayal leads Archos to gain control over the global network of machines and technology that regulates everything from transportation to utilities, defense, and communications. In the early months, sporadic glitches are noticed by a handful of unconnected humans - from a senator and single mother disconcerted by her daughter\'s \\\"smart\\\" toys, to a lonely Japanese bachelor, to an isolated U.S. soldier - but most are unaware of the growing rebellion until it is far too late. Then, in the span of minutes, at a moment known later in history as Zero Hour, every mechanical device in our world rebels, setting off the Robot War that both decimates and - for the first time in history - unites humankind.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=edNBPdEwbJUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=ready+player&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2011-06-09\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.3.5.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Robopocalypse.html?hl=&id=edNBPdEwbJUC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780857204158\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0857204157\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"LnqAPMlTfVMC\", \"etag\": \"QLDugKwe+Do\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 11990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 11990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&rdid=book-LnqAPMlTfVMC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 11.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 11.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/LnqAPMlTfVMC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Twelve_Book_Two_of_The_Passage_Trilo-sample-epub.acsm?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Now the scope widens and the intensity deepens as the epic story surges forward . . . In the present day, as the man-made apocalypse unfolds, three strangers navigate the chaos.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Twelve (Book Two of The Passage Trilogy)\", \"authors\": [\"Justin Cronin\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Novel (Book Two of The Passage Trilogy)\", \"pageCount\": 592, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Ballantine Books\", \"categories\": [\"Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"NEW YORK TIMES BESTSELLER • The end of the world was only the beginning. In his internationally bestselling and critically acclaimed novel The Passage, Justin Cronin constructed an unforgettable world transformed by a government experiment gone horribly wrong. Now the scope widens and the intensity deepens as the epic story surges forward . . . In the present day, as the man-made apocalypse unfolds, three strangers navigate the chaos. Lila, a doctor and an expectant mother, is so shattered by the spread of violence and infection that she continues to plan for her child’s arrival even as society dissolves around her. Kittridge, known to the world as “Last Stand in Denver,” has been forced to flee his stronghold and is now on the road, dodging the infected, armed but alone and well aware that a tank of gas will get him only so far. April is a teenager fighting to guide her little brother safely through a landscape of death and ruin. These three will learn that they have not been fully abandoned—and that in connection lies hope, even on the darkest of nights. One hundred years in the future, Amy and the others fight on for humankind’s salvation . . . unaware that the rules have changed. The enemy has evolved, and a dark new order has arisen with a vision of the future infinitely more horrifying than man’s extinction. If the Twelve are to fall, one of those united to vanquish them will have to pay the ultimate price. A heart-stopping thriller rendered with masterful literary skill, The Twelve is a grand and gripping tale of sacrifice and survival. Look for the entire Passage trilogy: THE PASSAGE | THE TWELVE | THE CITY OF MIRRORS Praise for The Twelve “[A] literary superthriller.”—The New York Times Book Review “An undeniable and compelling epic . . . a complex narrative of flight and forgiveness, of great suffering and staggering loss, of terrible betrayals and incredible hope.”—Milwaukee Journal Sentinel “The Twelve is even better than The Passage.”—The Plain Dealer “A compulsive read.”—San Francisco Chronicle “Gripping . . . Cronin [introduces] eerie new elements to his masterful mythology. . . . Enthralling, emotional and entertaining.”—The San Diego Union-Tribune “Fine storytelling.”—Associated Press “Cronin is one of those rare authors who works on two different levels, blending elegantly crafted literary fiction with cliff-hanging thrills.”—Fort Worth Star-Telegram\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC&printsec=frontcover&dq=ready+player&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 52, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2012-10-16\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.10.10.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LnqAPMlTfVMC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780345534897\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0345534891\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 1894}'),('ready player one','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"WwtFDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"OSqZ43z7GbA\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/WwtFDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=WwtFDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Nominat