e surgical procedures and expands coverage of zoonotic disease.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Ferrets, Rabbits and Rodents - E-Book\", \"authors\": [\"Katherine Quesenberry\", \"James W. Carpenter\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=VvICUGYAWtUC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Clinical Medicine and Surgery\", \"pageCount\": 608, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Elsevier Health Sciences\", \"categories\": [\"Medical\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VvICUGYAWtUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VvICUGYAWtUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"A concise guide to the care of small mammals, Ferrets, Rabbits, and Rodents: Clinical Medicine and Surgery covers the conditions seen most often in veterinary practice. The book emphasizes preventive medicine along with topics including disease management, ophthalmology, dentistry, and zoonosis. More than 400 illustrations demonstrate key concepts related to radiographic interpretation, relevant anatomy, and diagnostic, surgical, and therapeutic techniques. Now in full color, this edition adds coverage of more surgical procedures and expands coverage of zoonotic disease. From editors Katherine Quesenberry and James W. Carpenter, along with a team of expert contributors, the \\\"Pink Book\\\" provides an authoritative, single source of information that is hard to find elsewhere. A logical organization makes it quick and easy to find important information, with each section devoted to a single animal and chapters within each section organized by body system. Over 400 photographs and illustrations highlight key concepts such as radiographic interpretation and the main points of diagnostic, surgical, and therapeutic techniques. A chapter on ophthalmology provides hard-to-find information on eye care for ferrets, rabbits, rodents, and other small mammals. Coverage of preventive medicine includes basic biology, husbandry, and routine care of the healthy animal. The drug formulary supplies dosage instructions for ferrets, rabbits, guinea pigs, chinchillas, hamsters, rats/mice, prairie dogs, hedgehogs, and sugar gliders. Chapter outlines offer at-a-glance overviews of the contents of each chapter. Handy tables and charts make it easy to find key information. Expanded Zoonotic Diseases chapter adds more depth along with the latest information on the rising potential for disease transmission to humans as exotic pets become more popular. Additional surgical procedures for each species are included, some with step-by-step instructions accompanied by color photographs and line drawings. Full-color images show the sometimes minute structures of these small animals and make accurate diagnoses easier, especially for lymphoproliferative diseases of rabbits, endoscopy, cytology, and hematology.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=VvICUGYAWtUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=rodents&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2011-05-12\", \"contentVersion\": \"2.16.10.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=VvICUGYAWtUC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781437702880\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1437702880\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"OQJslIQON1EC\", \"etag\": \"qdDOXzMfqUc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 10990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 10990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=OQJslIQON1EC&rdid=book-OQJslIQON1EC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 10.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 10.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/OQJslIQON1EC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Amazing_Maurice_and_His_Educated_Rod-sample-epub.acsm?id=OQJslIQON1EC&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=OQJslIQON1EC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"For this is a town where food is scarce and rats are hated, where cellars are lined with deadly traps, and where a terrifying evil lurks beneath the hunger-stricken streets.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Amazing Maurice and His Educated Rodents\", \"authors\": [\"Terry Pratchett\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=OQJslIQON1EC&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 368, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Harper Collins\", \"categories\": [\"Young Adult Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OQJslIQON1EC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OQJslIQON1EC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Carnegie Medal Winner * New York Public Library Books for the Teen Age * VOYA Best Science Fiction, Fantasy, and Horror * ALA Best Fiction for Young Adults * Book Sense Pick The Amazing Maurice runs the perfect Pied Piper scam. This streetwise alley cat knows the value of cold, hard cash and can talk his way into and out of anything. But when Maurice and his cohorts decide to con the town of Bad Blinitz, it will take more than fast talking to survive the danger that awaits. For this is a town where food is scarce and rats are hated, where cellars are lined with deadly traps, and where a terrifying evil lurks beneath the hunger-stricken streets.... Set in Terry Pratchett\'s beloved Discworld, this masterfully crafted, gripping read is both compelling and funny. When one of the world\'s most acclaimed fantasy writers turns a classic fairy tale on its head, no one will ever look at the Pied Piper—or rats—the same way again!\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=OQJslIQON1EC&printsec=frontcover&dq=rodents&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 62, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2009-10-06\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.2.2.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=OQJslIQON1EC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780061975158\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"006197515X\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"3Cm6CAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"TT1vnF5SztQ\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/3Cm6CAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=3Cm6CAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Dentistry in Rabbits and Rodents is a practical guide aimed at helping clinicians successfully diagnose and treat dental problems in rabbits and rodents within their own surgeries.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Dentistry in Rabbits and Rodents\", \"authors\": [\"Estella Böhmer\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=3Cm6CAAAQBAJ&dq=rodents&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 296, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"John Wiley & Sons\", \"categories\": [\"Medical\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3Cm6CAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3Cm6CAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Dentistry in Rabbits and Rodents is a practical guide aimed at helping clinicians successfully diagnose and treat dental problems in rabbits and rodents within their own surgeries. With over two-thirds of small mammals presenting with tooth related problems, there is great potential to enhance the treatment offered to the owners of these species. Focusing on innovative diagnostics using normal radiographic machines as well as specific positioning techniques, radiographs are presented with reference lines and detailed annotations. Richly illustrated with high quality photographs, pathological findings are described before selection of appropriate therapy and treatment is discussed. Key features include: Covers the dental anatomy and physiology of all small mammal species commonly kept as pets. Intraoral radiography and innovative positioning for imaging the guinea pig and chinchilla dentitions are described, enabling the practitioner to visualize each tooth in detail. Once a diagnosis has been reached, selection of different treatments and the advantages and disadvantages of each surgical technique are discussed. Offers helpful directives for approaching and treating dental disease without the need for referral to a specialist or the use of expensive equipment.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=3Cm6CAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=rodents&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2015-04-27\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.2.0.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Dentistry_in_Rabbits_and_Rodents.html?hl=&id=3Cm6CAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781118802540\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1118802543\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"XtkldmBVVAwC\", \"etag\": \"f265iiyv9/M\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/XtkldmBVVAwC\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=XtkldmBVVAwC&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"With the help of extensive data tables and figures, this book explains the key facets of rodent thermal physiology, including neurological control and gender and intraspecies variations.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Temperature Regulation in Laboratory Rodents\", \"authors\": [\"Christopher J. Gordon\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=XtkldmBVVAwC&dq=rodents&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 276, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Cambridge University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Medical\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XtkldmBVVAwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XtkldmBVVAwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"With the help of extensive data tables and figures, this book explains the key facets of rodent thermal physiology, including neurological control and gender and intraspecies variations. The book should therefore find use in government, academic or industrial laboratories whose researchers are working with rodents.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=XtkldmBVVAwC&printsec=frontcover&dq=rodents&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"1993-08-27\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.6.1.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Temperature_Regulation_in_Laboratory_Rod.html?hl=&id=XtkldmBVVAwC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780521414265\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0521414261\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"1KOQDAEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"PYdKBxBn3rI\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/1KOQDAEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webRea