ans\", \"authors\": [\"Geoffrey A. Hosking\", \"Emeritus Professor of Russian History Geoffrey Hosking\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=oh-5AAmboMUC&dq=russia&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A History\", \"pageCount\": 718, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Harvard University Press\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oh-5AAmboMUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oh-5AAmboMUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Chronicles the history of the Russian Empire from the Mongol Invasion, through the Bolshevik Revolution, to the aftereffects of the Cold War.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=oh-5AAmboMUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=russia&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 2, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 5, \"publishedDate\": \"2001\", \"contentVersion\": \"3.4.4.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Russia_and_the_Russians.html?hl=&id=oh-5AAmboMUC\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0674004736\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780674004733\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"i2yYDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"HLO2zNrQv5U\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/i2yYDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=i2yYDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Russian Orthodoxy Resurgent is the first book to fully explore the expansive and ill-understood role that Russia&#39;s ancient Christian faith has played in the fall of Soviet Communism and in the rise of Russian nationalism today.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Russian Orthodoxy Resurgent\", \"authors\": [\"John Garrard\", \"Carol Garrard\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=i2yYDwAAQBAJ&dq=russia&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Faith and Power in the New Russia\", \"pageCount\": 326, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Princeton University Press\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=i2yYDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=i2yYDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Russian Orthodoxy Resurgent is the first book to fully explore the expansive and ill-understood role that Russia\'s ancient Christian faith has played in the fall of Soviet Communism and in the rise of Russian nationalism today. John and Carol Garrard tell the story of how the Orthodox Church\'s moral weight helped defeat the 1991 coup against Gorbachev launched by Communist Party hardliners. The Soviet Union disintegrated, leaving Russians searching for a usable past. The Garrards reveal how Patriarch Aleksy II--a former KGB officer and the man behind the church\'s successful defeat of the coup--is reconstituting a new national idea in the church\'s own image. In the new Russia, the former KGB who run the country--Vladimir Putin among them--proclaim the cross, not the hammer and sickle. Meanwhile, a majority of Russians now embrace the Orthodox faith with unprecedented fervor. The Garrards trace how Aleksy orchestrated this transformation, positioning his church to inherit power once held by the Communist Party and to become the dominant ethos of the military and government. They show how the revived church under Aleksy prevented mass violence during the post-Soviet turmoil, and how Aleksy astutely linked the church with the army and melded Russian patriotism and faith. Russian Orthodoxy Resurgent argues that the West must come to grips with this complex and contradictory resurgence of the Orthodox faith, because it is the hidden force behind Russia\'s domestic and foreign policies today.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=i2yYDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=russia&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2014-09-22\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.1.0.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Russian_Orthodoxy_Resurgent.html?hl=&id=i2yYDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780691165905\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0691165904\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"Ysm4DwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"QGxAb6hS8S0\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/Ysm4DwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=Ysm4DwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"This book analyzes the evolution of Russian military thought and how Russia&#39;s current thinking about war is reflected in recent crises.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Russian Understanding of War\", \"authors\": [\"Oscar Jonsson\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Ysm4DwAAQBAJ&dq=russia&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Blurring the Lines between War and Peace\", \"pageCount\": 200, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Georgetown University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Political Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ysm4DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ysm4DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"This book analyzes the evolution of Russian military thought and how Russia\'s current thinking about war is reflected in recent crises. While other books describe current Russian practice, Oscar Jonsson provides the long view to show how Russian military strategic thinking has developed from the Bolshevik Revolution to the present. He closely examines Russian primary sources including security doctrines and the writings and statements of Russian military theorists and political elites. What Jonsson reveals is that Russia\'s conception of the very nature of war is now changing, as Russian elites see information warfare and political subversion as the most important ways to conduct contemporary war. Since information warfare and political subversion are below the traditional threshold of armed violence, this has blurred the boundaries between war and peace. Jonsson also finds that Russian leaders have, particularly since 2011/12, considered themselves to be at war with the United States and its allies, albeit with non-violent means. This book provides much needed context and analysis to be able to understand recent Russian interventions in Crimea and eastern Ukraine, how to deter Russia on the eastern borders of NATO, and how the West must also learn to avoid inadvertent escalation.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=Ysm4DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=russia&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": false}, \"publishedDate\": \"2019-11-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.4.0.0.preview.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Russian_Understanding_of_War.html?hl=&id=Ysm4DwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781626167346\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1626167346\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"u4pIDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"Uxlu3cURf7g\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 9990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 7990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=u4pIDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-u4pIDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 9.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 7.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/u4pIDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Russia_Without_Putin-sample-epub.acsm?id=u4pIDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=u4pIDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Russia without Putin concludes by assessing the current regime’s prospects, and looks ahead to what the future may hold for the country.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Russia Without Putin\", \"authors\": [\"Tony Wood\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=u4pIDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Money, Power and the Myths of the New Cold War\", \"pageCount\": 224, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Verso Books\", \"categories\": [\"Political Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u4pIDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u4pIDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"How the West’s obsession with Vladimir Putin prevents it from understanding Russia It is impossible to think of Russia today without thinking of Vladimir Putin. More than any other major national leader, he personifies his country in the eyes of the world, and dominates Western media coverage. In Russia itself, he is likewise the centre of attention both for his supporters and his detractors. But, as Tony Wood argues, this focus on Russia’s president gets in the way of any real understanding of the country. The West needs to shake off its obsession with Putin and look beyond the Kremlin walls. In this timely and provocative analysis, Wood explores the profound changes Russia has undergone since 1991. In the process, he challenges several common assumptions made about contemporary Russia. Against the idea that Putin represents a return to Soviet authoritarianism, Wood argues that his rule should be seen as a 