\"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=W22DAgAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED_FOR_ACCESSIBILITY\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Ilan Berman shows the future of the country as grim and on the fast track to complete ruination. Is the end in sight for this former superpower?\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Implosion\", \"authors\": [\"Ilan Berman\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=W22DAgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"The End of Russia and What It Means for America\", \"pageCount\": 256, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Simon and Schuster\", \"categories\": [\"Political Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=W22DAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=W22DAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Crises—political, social, and economic—run rampant within Mother Russia’s borders. Russian troops infiltrate the Crimean peninsula, the UN Security Council attempts to mediate concerning the conflict with Ukraine, and the United States pledges aid to former Soviet satellites—and civil war teeters on the brink of eruption. In the wake of the Sochi Olympics, it is Russia that is skating on thin ice, and Vladimir Putin’s autonomous regime looks shakier by the minute. Ilan Berman shows the future of the country as grim and on the fast track to complete ruination. Is the end in sight for this former superpower? InImplosion, Berman explains why Russia’s collapse is imminent and how this nation’s ultimate demise will vitiate the United States.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=W22DAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=russia&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCoun