_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Bottom-Up Revolution to Rebuild American Prosperity\", \"pageCount\": 256, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"John Wiley & Sons\", \"categories\": [\"Business & Economics\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sSSpDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sSSpDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"A new way forward for sustainable quality of life in cities of all sizes Strong Towns: A Bottom-Up Revolution to Build American Prosperity is a book of forward-thinking ideas that breaks with modern wisdom to present a new vision of urban development in the United States. Presenting the foundational ideas of the Strong Towns movement he co-founded, Charles Marohn explains why cities of all sizes continue to struggle to meet their basic needs, and reveals the new paradigm that can solve this longstanding problem. Inside, you’ll learn why inducing growth and development has been the conventional response to urban financial struggles—and why it just doesn’t work. New development and high-risk investing don’t generate enough wealth to support itself, and cities continue to struggle. Read this book to find out how cities large and small can focus on bottom-up investments to minimize risk and maximize their ability to strengthen the community financially and improve citizens’ quality of life. Develop in-depth knowledge of the underlying logic behind the “traditional” search for never-ending urban growth Learn practical solutions for ameliorating financial struggles through low-risk investment and a grassroots focus Gain insights and tools that can stop the vicious cycle of budget shortfalls and unexpected downturns Become a part of the Strong Towns revolution by shifting the focus away from top-down growth toward rebuilding American prosperity Strong Towns acknowledges that there is a problem with the American approach to growth and shows community leaders a new way forward. The Strong Towns response is a revolution in how we assemble the places we live.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=sSSpDwAAQBAJ&pg=PR1&dq=towns&hl=&cd=1&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2019-10-01\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.1.0.0.preview.1\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Strong_Towns.html?hl=&id=sSSpDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781119564812\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1119564816\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"eKo_EAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"kmiVQYjDPh0\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 15000000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 15000000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eKo_EAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 15, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 15, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/eKo_EAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Confessions_of_a_Recovering_Engineer-sample-pdf.acsm?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Confessions_of_a_Recovering_Engineer-sample-epub.acsm?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Praise for CONFESSIONS OF A RECOVERING ENGINEER “I’ve been waiting for this book for a long time. It’s been more than a decade since its title essay rocked me to my core; reading it was my Meg Ryan When Harry Met Sally moment.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Confessions of a Recovering Engineer\", \"authors\": [\"Charles L. Marohn, Jr.\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Transportation for a Strong Town\", \"pageCount\": 272, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"John Wiley & Sons\", \"categories\": [\"Business & Economics\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Discover insider secrets of how America’s transportation system is designed, funded, and built – and how to make it work for your community In Confessions of a Recovering Engineer: Transportation for a Strong Town, renowned speaker and author of Strong Towns Charles L. Marohn Jr. delivers an accessible and engaging exploration of America’s transportation system, laying bare the reasons why it no longer works as it once did, and how to modernize transportation to better serve local communities. You’ll discover real-world examples of poor design choices and how those choices have dramatic and tragic effects on the lives of the people who use them. You’ll also find case studies and examples of design improvements that have revitalized communities and improved safety. This important book shows you: The values of the transportation professions, how they are applied in the design process, and how those priorities differ from those of the public. How the standard approach to transportation ensures the maximum amount of traffic congestion possible is created each day, and how to fight that congestion on a budget. Bottom-up techniques for spending less and getting higher returns on transportation projects, all while improving quality of life for residents. Perfect for anyone interested in why transportation systems work – and fail to work – the way they do, Confessions of a Recovering Engineer is a fascinating insider’s peek behind the scenes of America’s transportation systems.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=towns&hl=&cd=2&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-08-26\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eKo_EAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781119699255\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1119699258\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"9MwvDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"FbeRDcb8RZ8\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 13990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-9MwvDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 13.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/9MwvDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Our_Towns-sample-epub.acsm?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Our Towns is the story of their journey—and an account of a country busy remaking itself.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Our Towns\", \"authors\": [\"James Fallows\", \"Deborah Fallows\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A 100,000-Mile Journey into the Heart of America\", \"pageCount\": 432, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Vintage\", \"categories\": [\"Travel\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"NATIONAL BEST SELLER • The basis for the HBO documentary now streaming on HBO Max For five years, James and Deborah Fallows have travelled across America in a single-engine prop airplane. Visiting dozens of towns, the America they saw is acutely conscious of its problems—from economic dislocation to the opioid scourge—but it is also crafting solutions, with a practical-minded determination at dramatic odds with the bitter paralysis of national politics. At times of dysfunction on a national level, reform possibilities have often arisen from the local level. The Fallowses describe America in the middle of one of these creative waves. Their view of the country is as complex and contradictory as America itself, but it also reflects the energy, the generosity and compassion, the dreams, and the determination of many who are in the midst of making things better. Our Towns is the story of their journey—and an account of a country busy remaking itself.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=towns&hl=&cd=3&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 4, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": false}, \"averageRating\": 3.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2018-05-08\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.3.4.0.preview.2\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9MwvDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781101871850\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1101871857\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"YN9aDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"waYuFw20+x4\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 22990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 22990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=YN9aDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-YN9aDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 22.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 22.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/YN9aDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"