 of marked attraction, such as Ureña in Spain or Fjaerland in Norway, where bookshops have been set up in buildings including former ferry waiting rooms and banks. While the UK has the best-known examples at Hay, Wigtown and Sedbergh, the book has a broad international appeal, featuring locations such as Jimbochu in Japan, College Street in Calcutta, and major unofficial “book cities” such as Buenos Aires.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=YN9aDwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=towns&hl=&cd=4&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 4, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 4.5, \"publishedDate\": \"2018-04-05\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.2.3.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=YN9aDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781781012420\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1781012423\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"FyEuDwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"ZX7soHPRIJo\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 52950000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 42360000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-FyEuDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 52.95, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 42.36, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/FyEuDwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Geography_of_Towns-sample-pdf.acsm?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/The_Geography_of_Towns-sample-epub.acsm?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"When first released much praise was given to this book: &quot;An outstanding book on urban geography. . . representative of the best on this subject.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"The Geography of Towns\", \"authors\": [\"Arthur E. Smailes\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 160, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Routledge\", \"categories\": [\"Science\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"When first released much praise was given to this book: \\\"An outstanding book on urban geography. . . representative of the best on this subject.\\\"--Higher Education Journal \\\"The book ought to be required reading for every planner and student of planning . . . a magnificent achievement.\\\" --Town and Country Planning. The Geography of Towns provides a concise but thorough introduction to the important subject of urban geography. It traces the development of urban areas from the earliest sites of Nineveh, Aleppo, and Agade to modern megalopolises and strip cities, and deals authoritatively with problems of classification and ranking, location and type, origins, and course of development, and the relationship of the city to its region and nation. All facets of urban geography are covered, including the core, integuments, population structure, land-use patterns, enclaves, and town structure. Population mobility and the continual crisscross circulation of populations within and between town and region are seen as important forces affecting the internal geography of towns. The author questions the usefulness or validity of such terms as \\\"neighborhood\\\" and stresses the need for more meaningful conceptualizations and vocabulary. One of the fundamental problems connected with urban geography is to assist in the planning of future cities. This book contributes substantially to an understanding of the interrelations of town and region and to an understanding of the components of the city itself which are essential to intelligent planning for the future.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=towns&hl=&cd=5&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2017-07-12\", \"contentVersion\": \"0.0.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=FyEuDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781351482196\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"135148219X\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"nwo1EAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"3VspvqdKbE4\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/nwo1EAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Colonial_Life-sample-epub.acsm?id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"Easy-to-read chapters featuring full-color maps and illustrations take students from the early days of discovery and exploration, through the establishment of the first colonies by the vying European powers, to the events leading to the ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Colonial Life\", \"authors\": [\"Rebecca Stefoff\", \"Kathryn Hinds\", \"Linda Jacobs Altman\", \"Martin Kelly\", \"Melissa Kelly\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ&dq=towns&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Cities and Towns\", \"pageCount\": 96, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Routledge\", \"categories\": [\"Business & Economics\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"Aimed at readers ages 12 and up, the brand new \\\"Colonial Life\\\" series complements the world history and American history curriculum and follows the National Standards guidelines. Easy-to-read chapters featuring full-color maps and illustrations take students from the early days of discovery and exploration, through the establishment of the first colonies by the vying European powers, to the events leading to the Revolutionary War and the founding of the United States.Comprehensive in scope, the series covers events in North, Central, and South America, including the early settlements, the thirteen British colonies, Canada, the Spanish possessions of the southwest and California, and the French territories. Thematic volumes introduce students to daily life on the settlements, the diversity of the people, rule of government, religions and beliefs, and the regional and global economies involving trade and commerce. Coverage also includes material on Native American cultural groups from the pre-Columbian era through their interactions with the European colonists and settlers.Feature boxes and sidebars in each volume discuss high interest events and developments and offer biographical information, and primary source material displays historical documents along with quoted text from important figures and excerpts of their writing. A glossary and a guide to further information including Internet resources help make this set an invaluable addition to any school or public library.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=towns&hl=&cd=6&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2020-08-14\", \"contentVersion\": \"preview-1.0.0\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://books.google.com/books/about/Colonial_Life.html?hl=&id=nwo1EAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781317474135\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1317474139\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"gdJOzQEACAAJ\", \"etag\": \"/Q8oqT2uESs\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": false, \"saleability\": \"NOT_FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/gdJOzQEACAAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": false}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": false, \"viewability\": \"NO_PAGES\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=gdJOzQEACAAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"NONE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"When the first volume of this book was published in 2011, Strong Towns was a fledgling nonprofit.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Thoughts on Building Strong Towns\", \"authors\": [\"Charles L. Marohn (Jr.)\"], \"infoLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=gdJOzQEACAAJ&dq=towns&hl=&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 184, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"categories\": [\"BUSINESS & ECONOMICS\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gdJOzQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gdJOzQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"When the first volume of this book was published in 2011, Strong Towns was a fledgling nonprofit. Since then, it has grown into a national media organization with an award-winning website, StrongTowns.org, and accompanying podcast. Over the last five years, Strong Towns\' member base has grown and its message has spread across the country. Volume II is a chance to share the top essays published on our website in 2015, reworked and compiled into compelling chapters including, \\\"Can you be an engineer and speak out for reform?\\\" \\\"Dealing with Congestion,\\\" and \\\"My Car Pays Cheaper Rent Than Me.\\\" Also included are sections on Strong Towns\' ongoing campaigns, #NoNewRoads and #SlowtheCars. The book features writing from Strong Towns\' president, Charles Marohn, as well as several Strong Towns contributors.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=gdJOzQEACAAJ&dq=towns&hl=&cd=7&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": false,