fo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"&quot;Powerful and important . . . an instant classic.&quot; —The Washington Post Book World The award-winning look at an ugly aspect of American racism by the bestselling author of Lies My Teacher Told Me, reissued with a new preface by the author ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Sundown Towns\", \"authors\": [\"James W. Loewen\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=abhIDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"A Hidden Dimension of American Racism\", \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"The New Press\", \"categories\": [\"History\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=abhIDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=abhIDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"\\\"Powerful and important . . . an instant classic.\\\" —The Washington Post Book World The award-winning look at an ugly aspect of American racism by the bestselling author of Lies My Teacher Told Me, reissued with a new preface by the author In this groundbreaking work, sociologist James W. Loewen, author of the classic bestseller Lies My Teacher Told Me, brings to light decades of hidden racial exclusion in America. In a provocative, sweeping analysis of American residential patterns, Loewen uncovers the thousands of \\\"sundown towns\\\"—almost exclusively white towns where it was an unspoken rule that blacks weren\'t welcome—that cropped up throughout the twentieth century, most of them located outside of the South. Written with Loewen\'s trademark honesty and thoroughness, Sundown Towns won the Gustavus Myers Outstanding Book Award, received starred reviews in Publishers Weekly and Booklist, and launched a nationwide online effort to track down and catalog sundown towns across America. In a new preface, Loewen puts this history in the context of current controversies around white supremacy and the Black Lives Matter movement. He revisits sundown towns and finds the number way down, but with notable exceptions in exclusive all-white suburbs such as Kenilworth, Illinois, which as of 2010 had not a single black household. And, although many former sundown towns are now integrated, they often face \\\"second-generation sundown town issues,\\\" such as in Ferguson, Missouri, a former sundown town that is now majority black, but with a majority-white police force.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=abhIDwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=towns&hl=&cd=8&source=gbs_api\", \"ratingsCount\": 4, \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"averageRating\": 4, \"publishedDate\": \"2018-07-17\", \"contentVersion\": \"2.5.5.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": true, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=abhIDwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9781620974544\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"1620974541\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"LRQLEAAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"onNdbE9XR2I\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 10990000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 10990000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-LRQLEAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 10.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 10.99, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/LRQLEAAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/My_Two_Border_Towns-sample-pdf.acsm?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/My_Two_Border_Towns-sample-epub.acsm?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"My Two Border Towns by David Bowles, with stunning watercolor illustrations by Erika Meza, is the loving story of a father and son&#39;s weekend ritual, a demonstration of community care, and a tribute to the fluidity, complexity, and vibrancy ...\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"My Two Border Towns\", \"authors\": [\"David Bowles\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"pageCount\": 40, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Penguin\", \"categories\": [\"Juvenile Fiction\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"A picture book debut by an award-winning author about a boy\'s life on the U.S.-Mexico border, visiting his favorite places on The Other Side with his father, spending time with family and friends, and sharing in the responsibility of community care. Early one Saturday morning, a boy prepares for a trip to The Other Side/El Otro Lado. It\'s close--just down the street from his school--and it\'s a twin of where he lives. To get there, his father drives their truck along the Rio Grande and over a bridge, where they\'re greeted by a giant statue of an eagle. Their outings always include a meal at their favorite restaurant, a visit with Tío Mateo at his jewelry store, a cold treat from the paletero, and a pharmacy pickup. On their final and most important stop, they check in with friends seeking asylum and drop off much-needed supplies. My Two Border Towns by David Bowles, with stunning watercolor illustrations by Erika Meza, is the loving story of a father and son\'s weekend ritual, a demonstration of community care, and a tribute to the fluidity, complexity, and vibrancy of life on the U.S.-Mexico border. Available in English and Spanish.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=towns&hl=&cd=9&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2021-09-14\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.1.1.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LRQLEAAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780593111055\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0593111052\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}, {\"id\": \"-Jv3AwAAQBAJ\", \"etag\": \"dUGbPWjGEhc\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\", \"saleInfo\": {\"offers\": [{\"giftable\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 28000000}, \"retailPrice\": {\"currencyCode\": \"USD\", \"amountInMicros\": 15120000}, \"finskyOfferType\": 1}], \"buyLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&rdid=book--Jv3AwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api\", \"country\": \"US\", \"isEbook\": true, \"listPrice\": {\"amount\": 28, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"retailPrice\": {\"amount\": 15.12, \"currencyCode\": \"USD\"}, \"saleability\": \"FOR_SALE\"}, \"selfLink\": \"https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes/-Jv3AwAAQBAJ\", \"accessInfo\": {\"pdf\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Boom_Towns-sample-pdf.acsm?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&format=pdf&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"epub\": {\"isAvailable\": true, \"acsTokenLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books/download/Boom_Towns-sample-epub.acsm?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&format=epub&output=acs4_fulfillment_token&dl_type=sample&source=gbs_api\"}, \"country\": \"US\", \"embeddable\": true, \"viewability\": \"PARTIAL\", \"publicDomain\": false, \"webReaderLink\": \"http://play.google.com/books/reader?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&hl=&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_api\", \"accessViewStatus\": \"SAMPLE\", \"quoteSharingAllowed\": false, \"textToSpeechPermission\": \"ALLOWED\"}, \"searchInfo\": {\"textSnippet\": \"In Boom Towns, Stephen J.K. Walters diagnoses the root causes of urban decline in order to prescribe remedies that will enable cities to thrive once again.\"}, \"volumeInfo\": {\"title\": \"Boom Towns\", \"authors\": [\"Stephen J.K. Walters\"], \"infoLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api\", \"language\": \"en\", \"subtitle\": \"Restoring the Urban American Dream\", \"pageCount\": 224, \"printType\": \"BOOK\", \"publisher\": \"Stanford University Press\", \"categories\": [\"Business & Economics\"], \"imageLinks\": {\"thumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\", \"smallThumbnail\": \"http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=5&edge=curl&source=gbs_api\"}, \"description\": \"American cities, once economic and social launch pads for their residents, are all too often plagued by poverty and decay. One need only to look at the ruins of Detroit to see how far some once-great cities have fallen, or at Boston and San Francisco for evidence that such decline is reversible. In Boom Towns, Stephen J.K. Walters diagnoses the root causes of urban decline in order to prescribe remedies that will enable cities to thrive once again. Arguing that commonplace explanations for urban decay misunderstand the nature of our towns, Walters reconceives of cities as dense accumulations of capital in all of its forms—places that attract people by making their labor more productive and their leisure more pleasurable. Policymakers, therefore, must properly define and enforce property rights in order to prevent the flight of capital and the resulting demise of urban centers. Using vivid evocations of iconic towns and the people who crucially affected their destinies, Walters shows how public policy measures which aim to revitalize often do more harm than good. He then outlines a more promising set of policies to remedy the capital shortage that continues to afflict many cities and needlessly limit their residents\' opportunities. With its fresh interpretation of one of the American quandaries of our day, Boom Towns offers a novel contribution to the debate about American cities and a program for their restoration.\", \"previewLink\": \"http://books.google.com/books?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=towns&hl=&cd=10&source=gbs_api\", \"readingModes\": {\"text\": true, \"image\": true}, \"publishedDate\": \"2014-08-27\", \"contentVersion\": \"1.4.5.0.preview.3\", \"maturityRating\": \"NOT_MATURE\", \"allowAnonLogging\": false, \"canonicalVolumeLink\": \"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-Jv3AwAAQBAJ\", \"industryIdentifiers\": [{\"type\": \"ISBN_13\", \"identifier\": \"9780804792271\"}, {\"type\": \"ISBN_10\", \"identifier\": \"0804792275\"}], \"panelizationSummary\": {\"containsEpubBubbles\": false, \"containsImageBubbles\": false}}}], \"totalItems\": 3131}'),('ufos','{\"kind\": \"books#volumes\", \"items\": [{\"id\": \"Mzc6R2LH24kC\", \"etag\": \"6zGyo9rXmPs\", \"kind\": \"books#volume\